( agence france - presse , washington , 2 nd ) - u . s . newspaper reported today that pyongyang has authorized a u . s . delegation , including top nuclear scientists , to visit north korea 's yongbyon nuclear facilities next week .
members of the delegation told the us newspaper today that the bush administration had approved the us delegation 's scheduled visit to north korea from january 6 to 10 .
this will be the first visit by a foreign delegation to a disputed nuclear facility in north korea since un inspectors were expelled from north korea a year ago .
members of the us delegation include a chinese expert from stanford university , two foreign policy assistants from the senate , and a former state department official responsible for dealing with pyongyang .
the delegation 's nuclear experts , who led the national laboratory in the united states , were the first to develop the atomic bomb between 1985 and 1997 .
prior to this , north korea recently notified the us embassy in beijing that pyongyang was ready to attend the delay of the second round of six - party talks on the nuclear crisis on the korean peninsula .
us officials pointed out early this week that pyongyang has indicated that it is ready to attend the six - party talks to be held early this year .
no conclusion was reached at the end of the first round of six - party talks held in beijing in august last year . north korea later criticized the negotiations as " totally useless . "
the second round of six - party talks was originally scheduled to be held in december last year , but the talks were postponed to the beginning of this year because of the differences in the stance on the solution of the issue .
washington has demanded that north korea unilaterally abandon its nuclear weapons program , while pyongyang has insisted that the united states provide a legally binding security guarantee as a condition for it to abandon its nuclear development program .
