us starts to take photos of foreign visitors , keep fingerprints
( agence france - presse , washington , 5 th ) - at a time when singapore , the largest airport in asia , supports the deployment of air armed police to cope with terrorist threats , the united states today started to take pictures of foreign visitors and keep fingerprints .
in the past week , washington has been forced to cancel a number of flights to and from the united states at a time when global air safety concerns have been rising .
the new measures for taking photos and keeping fingerprints are only applicable to foreign visitors who need to obtain a visa to enter the united states , and it is generally expected that the total number of such visitors will reach 23 million this year .
the homeland security department , which is responsible for the implementation of the " us visitor and immigration identity display technology " project , pointed out that citizens of most 28 countries in europe are exempted from the above procedures .
immigration groups accused the plan of infringing on the freedom of citizens and a step toward building a monitoring society , and homeland security secretary ridge has spared no effort in defending the plan .
" one of the primary responsibilities of any government is to ensure the security of the border . we are promoting this program . i think it will not lose at all . in fact , it takes only about 15 seconds , and obviously no one will care about it . "
by 2005 , all the entry points of the land , sea , and air will be ready to take pictures and keep fingerprint technology .
all us visas and passports will eventually be included in " biological identification signs " including photos and fingerprints .
prior to the implementation of the plan , the united states has just raised the alert level of the united states to guard against the threat of terrorist attacks in december last year .
