( agence france - presse , seoul , 6 th ) south korea said today that a new round of six - nation nuclear talks may be postponed to mid - year due to the tough stance of north korea and the united states .
" i hope that the talks will be held in the first half of this year at the latest , " south korean foreign minister yin yongkuan told reporters when attending a cabinet meeting in tsing wa dae .
yin yongkuan made the above remarks after washington rejected pyongyang 's latest request for a major concession in exchange for a nuclear freeze and said that the two sides still had to resolve serious differences before the nuclear talks .
yin yongkuan said that the issue of the time arrangements for the six participating countries actually ruled out the possibility of resuming the six - nation talks in january .
however , he did not provide clues to why the new round of talks might be extended to or after june .
russian deputy foreign minister roosevelt attributed this to the hard - line attitude of the united states and north korea .
he participated in the first round of six - nation talks held in beijing in august last year .
after meeting with senior chinese officials yesterday , roosevelt told interfax news agency , " the reason is still the same as in the past -- the lack of trust between the two sides , and the demands raised by the two sides are too heavy . "
after north korea again demanded that the united states promise to make concessions before the new round of six - nation talks , yin yongkuan proposed the possibility of a long - term delay in the talks .
washington accused pyongyang of setting preconditions for a new round of six - nation talks .
the united states is seeking north korea 's promise to scrap its nuclear weapons program .
north korea said it would freeze its nuclear facilities if washington lifted economic sanctions against pyongyang and resumed energy aid .
in the past , north korea also insisted on signing a non - aggression treaty with the united states .
