( agence france - presse , islamabad , 6 th ) - the south asian summit closed today . during the summit , the two hostile nuclear powers of india and pakistan completed a breakthrough talks , and the participating countries signed a free trade agreement , which is of epoch - making significance to the south asian region .
at the closing session of the 12th south asian regional cooperation association ( saa ) summit , bangladesh 's prime minister girija said , " this summit is an important watershed in strengthening south asian regional cooperation . "
indian prime minister vajpayee and pakistani president pervez musharraf held the first meeting between the two countries since the nuclear war broke out in 2002 at the summit .
the hostility between the two major powers of the south asian regional cooperation association has hindered the development of the region , and the leaders of the participating countries are encouraged by the momentum of peace that has been brought about by the historic talks between india and pakistan .
" i think there has been a clear change in the positions of india and pakistan , and the two countries are moving toward the peace process , " pakistani military analyst mahmoud ahmadinejad told afp .
at the conclusion of the summit , pakistani prime minister jaswant singh praised the important agreement on the fight against terrorism , the easing of poverty , and the establishment of a regional free trade zone in 2006 .
he also praised the summit for " injecting new vitality into regional cooperation . "
the heads of state and foreign ministers of bangladesh , bhutan , india , malta , nepal , pakistan and sri lanka signed the south asia free trade zone agreement , the social charter , the anti - poverty program , the anti - terrorism agreement , and the " islamabad declaration " at the summit .
