health ministry officials detected bird flu viruses in this region on monday .
this is the first time in nine days that south korea has confirmed the discovery of avian flu virus .
last month , bird flu broke out in 15 parts of south korea , forcing the authorities to cull nearly two million chickens and ducks , and this highly infectious poultry disease was apparently under control .
" we culled all chickens in the epidemic area and strictly restricted the movement of these poultry , " said kim chang - kong , director of the animal health group of the south korean ministry of health .
the emergence of new cases of avian flu has prompted south korean government officials to strengthen quarantine in other areas .
the bird flu virus can survive for two weeks in the dust , and can survive at least 35 days in poultry faeces , kim said .
