us , japan optimistic about resumption of talks with north korea
( agence france - presse , washington , 22nd ) - u . s . said today that it is " very optimistic " about the resumption of multinational talks as soon as possible to end north korea 's nuclear deadlock . however , the u . s . also said that it is only making some progress in urging pyongyang to return to the conference table .
" we think there is great hope that the six - party talks will be resumed very soon , but we have no definite date yet , " said kelly , the top us diplomatic official in charge of asia - pacific affairs .
kelly held talks with senior officials from japan and south korea to discuss the situation of north korea 's nuclear development . he said that the possibility of holding the second round of talks is still very high , and that it will eventually urge north korea to agree to dissolve its nuclear program .
kelly told reporters : " we think it is very likely that the six - party talks will continue . "
however , he said that the agreement should be broad - based , including the guarantee that pyongyang is willing to accept verification , so as to thoroughly abolish the uranium enrichment program , reprocess plutonium , and deal with the existing atomic weapons .
north korea has produced the plutonium they said to us non - official representatives , but denied having any uranium enrichment program , and refuted the us claim that pyongyang had admitted that it had a uranium enrichment program during the 2002 talks .
who confirms sixth case of bird flu death in vietnam
( agence france - presse , hanoi , 24th ) - the world health organization ( who ) confirmed today the sixth case of bird flu death in vietnam . a 13 - year - old boy in southern vietnam 's ho chi minh city has died of avian flu virus infection .
this is the first confirmed case of bird flu death in southern vietnam .
vietnamese health officials announced earlier that the sixth case of avian flu had not been cured , bringing the death toll to at least six in vietnam , and making the outside world even more concerned about the spread of the virus and human problems .
the boy was tested positive for avian flu hat1 and confirmed to be infected with the virus .
the boy died on january 22 at the second children 's hospital in ho chi minh city , the health secretary of ho chi minh city , nguyen dy nien , told afp today .
he was sent to hospital on the 19 th for respiratory symptoms .
the world health organization also claimed that it is now working together with the vietnamese authorities to pay attention to the development of the epidemic .
another vietnamese health official pointed out that a pair of sisters died on the 22 nd in a hospital in hanoi due to serious respiratory illness , and the health authorities suspected that the two were also victims of avian flu .
millions of chickens and poultry suffer from bird flu in indonesia
( agence france - presse , jakarta , 25 th ) - indonesian agriculture ministry announced today that several million chickens have been killed in the bird flu epidemic , but so far there has been no report of human infection .
the head of the animal department of the ministry of agriculture , sudakar , told the public that no one in indonesia has been infected with the deadly disease so far .
at present , there are seven countries in asia where bird flu has been reported , and six people have died in vietnam .
indonesian officials earlier said that bird flu , which was commonly infected in poultry in java and bali last november , was a new city disease .
this morning , ministry of agriculture spokesman joseph prueher also said that there is no indication of a bird flu outbreak in indonesia .
in the evening , he told afp that it was not clear whether this wave of epidemic would trigger a hatch of the 5nik virus .
most of vietnam 's bird flu deaths were caused by the hatchet virus .
the spokesman said that the new city had caused 4.7 million deaths in poultry since november last year as a result of influenza a .
about 60 percent of them died of illness in the new city .
he said that no immediate culling had been ordered .
the indonesian state - run news agency quoted sudakar as saying that the authorities have used british and australian blood to test and confirm the types of the virus , but the test results may only be released on wednesday and thursday , and the government will submit a report to the relevant international organizations .
snow covers western europe , causes traffic and transport chaos
( agence france - presse , paris , 29 th ) - the snow - covered western europe and northern europe has caused great traffic and railway chaos and forced hundreds of flights from britain , germany and denmark to cancel .
in london , a spokesman for the airport said more than 200 flights were cancelled last night , and 80 flights were suspended early this morning .
the other two airports near london , which are affected by snow , have cancelled 18 flights due to weather conditions .
in germany , the winter weather led to the cancellation of at least 60 flights to frankfurt international airport , the biggest airport in germany .
air traffic may be affected by weather conditions for the rest of the day , the transport authorities said .
in france , the road traffic restrictions in paris have been lifted after a snowfall last night , but similar measures have been implemented in other parts of france .
it is reported that the services of the main paris airport are close to normal , and the flights of the de gaulle airport were delayed yesterday due to snow and fog .
however , the paris airport authorities suggested that passengers travelling in the air should first find out whether their flights would take off and land on time before they leave .
with the exception of the central coast , most parts of france are covered by snow .
