asia is the largest continent in the world , with an area of nearly 30 percent of the world 's land . at present , its population accounts for about 60 percent of the world 's total population , and its total economic volume accounts for one - fourth of the world 's total , and it should and can make outstanding contributions to world peace and development .
asia has a long - standing splendid culture , and the yellow river and the chang jiang valley , the indian river and the henghe river valley , the youdi river , and the chulls river are famous human civilizations .
in the long historical process , the asian people have written a brilliant chapter in the development of human civilization .
in modern times , asia has experienced many vicissitudes of life and has suffered repeated hardships , and the people of all countries have made unremitting efforts and made tremendous achievements to strive for liberation and development .
however , there is still a long way to go in order to achieve a new rise and rejuvenation in asia .
strengthening cooperation , promoting development , and realizing peace is the only way for the rise and rejuvenation of asia , and is also where the fundamental interests of the asian people lie .
under the new situation in the new century , asia 's development is facing new opportunities .
peace and development are still the main themes of the times , and the overall peaceful international environment has provided favorable external conditions for asia 's development .
the in - depth development of economic globalization , the rapid development of the world 's scientific and technological revolution , and the optimization and reorganization of international production factors and the acceleration of industrial transfer are conducive to asian countries ' use of international capital , introduction of advanced technology , opening up the international market , and promoting their own economic development .
asia is rich in resources and has a vast market , and is the region with the greatest economic vitality in the world today , and there is great potential for development .
a large population and an underdeveloped country are two major national conditions in china .
china has a population of 1.3 - billion , no matter how small the problem is , so long as we take advantage of 1.3 - billion , it will become a very big problem , and no matter how much financial and material resources are , it will become a very low per capita level .
this is something that the chinese leaders must firmly remember at any time .
to solve the problem of 1.3 billion people , we cannot rely on others but on ourselves .
since the founding of the people 's republic of china , great achievements have been made in our construction , and at the same time , we have also taken some detours and lost some opportunities .
since the beginning of reform and opening up in 1978 , we have finally found a correct way to develop ourselves .
this is : the chinese people independently and independently build socialism with chinese characteristics .
the essence of this road is to mobilize all positive factors , emancipate and develop productive forces , and respect and safeguard the freedom of the chinese people in pursuing happiness .
china 's reform and opening up , from rural areas to cities and from the economic field to the political , cultural , and social fields .
in the final analysis , every step of its deepening is aimed at giving free rein to the vitality of all labor , knowledge , technology , management , and capital , and allowing all the sources of creating social wealth to flow in full .
in recent years , profound changes have taken place in the world , science and technology have been changing with each passing day , the level of the world 's productive forces has been constantly raised , and the world market has become even closer , thus creating a historical opportunity for the development of various countries .
however , it is worth noting that power politics , regional conflicts , terrorism , infectious diseases , and environmental deterioration are still threatening world stability and development .
the negative impact of economic globalization has increased the risk and price of economic and social development in developing countries , and some developing countries are even facing the danger of being marginalized .
at present , although the world economy is gradually recovering , there are still many uncertainties .
the doha round of multilateral trade negotiations has suffered setbacks , and the complicated factors such as trade protectionism have increased the difficulties of developing countries .
what is gratifying is that the vast number of developing countries have made active efforts to forge ahead , have been keen on reform , and have made great efforts to make the country prosperous , and have achieved eye - catching results .
on the international stage , the developing countries , on the basis of the non-aligned movement and the 77 - nation group , have strengthened unity and cooperation , made important contributions to safeguarding their own legitimate rights and interests and changing the irrational international political and economic order , and become an important force for promoting the democratization of international relations .
at the same time , exchanges and cooperation between developing countries have also achieved fruitful results , and economic exchanges between them have become even more frequent .
the south - south cooperation has been constantly enriched , perfected , and updated from the antara mountain to the bank of the mekong river , from the ma - bu alliance to the establishment of the african union , from content to form , and from mechanism to means .
the past year has also been a year in which sino - canadian friendly and cooperative relations have continued to develop in an all - round way .
trade between the two countries has maintained a momentum of growth , and the total volume of trade is close to $ 10 billion .
high - level contacts have been frequent , and a number of important political figures , including the canadian foreign minister , the defense minister , the environment minister , and the minister of international cooperation , have visited china one after another , and the chinese supreme court president , the minister of commerce , and other senior officials have also visited canada . more importantly , the prime ministers of the two countries have successfully exchanged visits .
premier wen jiabao 's recent visit to canada has the significance of inheriting the past and forging ahead into the future , and has injected new vitality into the further development of sino - canadian relations , thus laying a solid foundation for the continuous development of friendly cooperation between the two countries in various fields .
china and canada will continue to strengthen cooperation in the political , economic , cultural , educational , and scientific and technological fields , and strive to achieve the goal of doubling the total volume of bilateral trade in 2010 .
