since the founding of new china , the chinese government has always attached great importance to developing relations with africa and formulated a series of principles and policies .
we have always adhered to the five principles of peaceful coexistence , respected the independent choice of political systems and development paths by african countries , provided assistance to african countries within our capacity , carried out economic and technological cooperation , supported the unity and cooperation of african countries , united and self-strengthening , promoted the international community 's attention to peace and development in africa , supported african countries in participating in international affairs on an equal footing , strengthened consultations and cooperation between china and africa , and jointly safeguarded the rights and interests of developing countries .
sino - african friendship goes back to ancient times and deeply rooted in the hearts of the people .
since the founding of new china , we have always firmly supported the cause of national liberation in africa and sincerely helped african countries develop their national economies .
chinese experts , doctors , teachers , and workers sent to africa work side by side with the local people , live in friendship , and have a good relationship with each other .
in international affairs , china and african countries understand and support each other and have become mutually trusted partners .
the chinese people will never forget that at the 26 th un general assembly in 1971 , china smoothly restored its legitimate seat in the united nations with the strong support of the vast number of developing countries , including african countries .
in recent years , the political mutual trust between the chinese and african personnel at all levels and in all fields has been constantly deepened , economic and trade cooperation has been fruitful , and friendly exchanges in the fields of culture , education , health , science and technology , and sports have been developing vigorously . the china - africa cooperation forum , which was established at the beginning of the century , has created a new platform for the development of sino - african relations and the deepening of cooperation .
china and africa have decided to establish a new - type partnership of long - term stability , equality , and mutual benefit , and sino - african friendly cooperation has entered a new stage of comprehensive development .
seven years after nixon 's visit to china and the issuance of the sino - us shanghai communique , the carter administration accepted china 's stand on the taiwan issue and realized the establishment of diplomatic relations between china and the united states .
this incident and deng xiaoping 's successful visit to the united states have opened a new chapter in sino - us relations .
in the early days of reagan 's administration , china and the united states had a fierce confrontation on the taiwan issue .
after arduous negotiations , the two governments issued the famous " 17 august " communique in 1982 and reached an agreement on the gradual settlement of the issue of arms sales to taiwan .
the shanghai communique , the sino - us communique on the establishment of diplomatic relations , and the " 17 august " communique jointly constitute the political cornerstone of sino - us relations .
in the 10 years since the establishment of diplomatic relations , although the two countries have waged struggles on the taiwan issue and other issues , sino - us relations have been stable on the whole , and exchanges and cooperation in various fields have increased day by day .
in the 1980 s and early 1990 's , the drastic changes in eastern europe , the breakup of the soviet union , and the end of the cold war , the most profound changes have taken place in the international situation since world war ii .
the united states has taken the lead in imposing sanctions on china , announced the sale of 150 - 16 fighter planes to taiwan , linked the human rights issue with the most favored nation treatment , and allowed lee teng - hui to visit the united states , with the result that sino - us relations have fallen to a low ebb .
with the rapid development of china 's economy , china 's international status has been constantly enhanced .
more and more people in the united states have realized that the improvement and development of sino - us relations conforms to the interests of both the united states and china .
half a year ago , in this hall , we successfully launched the six - party talks and established the direction of peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue .
over the past six months , the various parties have conducted endless dialogue and consultations , made a great deal of and in - depth preparations for the holding of a new round of talks , and , through this process , enhanced their understanding of each other 's stand .
at present , all parties are looking forward to the second round of talks to discuss substantive issues and achieve concrete results , and all agree to resolve their concerns through coordinated and consistent steps , and hope that the peace process opened up by the six - party talks will be maintained .
these have constituted an important foundation for our talks today .
the important significance of the second round of talks is to start discussions on substantive issues , which marks a new step forward in the peace talks .
the current round of talks will focus on how to establish a specific goal for resolving the nuclear issue , explore the first - stage measures for resolving the nuclear issue , and study the way to continue the talks .
along with the deepening of the talks , we will deal with more difficulties and meet more challenges , but this is precisely the duty entrusted by history and the expectation placed on us by the international community .
our six - party gathering here represents the strong political desire of the governments and peoples of the six countries to seek peace .
our talks were aimed at expanding consensus rather than highlighting differences , and at solving problems rather than intensifying contradictions .
the chinese side believes that all sides can realize the peace mission on their shoulders , respect each other , show flexibility , and narrow the gap with a constructive attitude and in the spirit of cooperation and understanding .
after more than three days of consultations , the second round of six - party talks in beijing completed the scheduled agenda .
i would like to thank the governments of various countries , their heads and representatives , and their staff for their contributions to this end .
if we say that the first round of talks has set the great goal of achieving a nuclear - free peninsula , then the significance of this round of talks is to conduct substantive dialogue and make a new step toward the realization of the great goal .
during the talks , all parties held in - depth and constructive discussions , and put forward valuable ideas and made positive policy statements with wisdom and rational exploration of methods and steps to resolve problems .
the talks have achieved a series of useful results , especially the consensus reached on the next round of talks and the establishment of a working group , which is of great significance to the promotion of the peace talks .
dear colleagues , peace and development are the themes of our great era .
the people of the six countries represented here need peace , peace , and peace , and the people of all countries in the world need peace , peace , and peace .
over the past three days , the international community has paid close attention to beijing , the diaoyutai , and placed high hopes on this round of talks .
some people may think that the results of the talks are not enough , and the process is not yet fast enough .
my view is that the current round of talks was launched at a time when the parties concerned lack mutual trust and the gap between their positions is widening .
the chinese government 's stand on the taiwan issue is consistent , that is , adhering to the basic principle of " peaceful reunification and one country , two systems . "
to this end , we have done all we can to show our greatest sincerity and done a lot of work .
however , our efforts have been challenged by the taiwan authorities and the " taiwan independence " forces .
we respect the democratic demands of the taiwan people , but we oppose the taiwan authorities and the " taiwan independence " forces engaging in " taiwan independence " activities in the name of democracy and splitting taiwan from the motherland .
the reason why we have clearly demonstrated our determination and will to safeguard the motherland 's reunification is to safeguard peace and stability in the taiwan strait region .
we have indicated that as long as there is a line of hope , we will do our best to realize the reunification of the motherland by peaceful means .
we appreciate that president bush once again reiterated his adherence to the one - china stand and sent a clear signal to the " taiwan independence " forces .
the leader of the taiwan authorities claimed that " in order to prevent china 's armed invasion of taiwan , it is necessary to unilaterally change the status quo between the two sides of the strait , and to promote a peaceful referendum of 320 . "
this is a slander against the mainland 's efforts for peace and a provocation against cross - strait relations .
at present , the actual threat to taiwan 's security is not from the mainland , but from the " taiwan independence " separatist activities carried out by the taiwan authorities in a big way .
" taiwan independence " separatist forces are the direct cause of undermining the status quo of cross - strait relations and endangering peace in the taiwan strait .
the taiwan authorities distorted the mainland 's opposition to " taiwan independence " separatism and the maintenance of stability in the taiwan strait as an excuse for suppressing taiwan 's democracy and freedom , and used this as an excuse for launching a referendum .
this is sheer fabrication and distortion of right and wrong , and is aimed at deceiving people with sympathy and support for their continued pursuit of the splittist line .
the leader of the taiwan authorities claimed that the so - called " defense referendum " and " peaceful referendum " will be held , but no matter how they are packaged , such provocative acts will only provoke cross - strait antagonism and hostility , aggravate cross - strait tension , and push cross - strait relations to the brink of danger step by step .
this completely runs counter to the mainstream public opinion of the taiwan compatriots in seeking peace , stability , and development , and is not the deepening of taiwan 's " democracy , " but is misleading and controlling the taiwan people , and is also a serious threat to peace and stability in the asia - pacific region , and is bound to be opposed by the compatriots on both sides of the strait and the international community .
taking a general look at the historical process of the development of the chinese nation , reunification has always been the mainstream , the trend of the times , and the desire of the people .
with the growing strength of the motherland , the continuous strengthening of cross - strait cooperation , and the general recognition of one china by the international community , the pattern of one china has been further consolidated , and any separatist attempt is doomed to failure .
another two weeks or so is the lunar new year , which is one of the most important traditional festivals for the chinese people .
on this exciting and happy day , we are accustomed to meeting with our relatives and friends and exchanging gifts to express our feelings .
in the spirit of " linking people and delivering business , " hongkong post is working with china post to launch this " china - hong kong gift fulfilment service " to send their greetings and best wishes to their relatives and friends in the mainland or in hong kong during the spring festival .
hongkong post has been working closely with other postal administrations to provide international courierpost services .
as early as december 2002 , australia post and australia post launched a wine logistics service to provide quality products to hong kong people .
this time , we have been working with china post to extend the close co - operation between the two sides in postal , postal remittance , and express delivery services to cross - boundary logistics services , and to launch the " china - hong kong gift fulfilment service " in response to the increasing market demand of hong kong residents to give gifts to their relatives and friends or customers in the mainland .
the first batch of gift sets was packed with a variety of exquisite lunar new year gift sets , including festive candies , tea leaves and dried seafood .
