over the past several hundred years since the birth of the intellectual property rights system , especially since the industrial revolution , it has given birth to one major invention after another of epoch - making significance .
in the past 20 years , the intellectual property system has become the basic legal system and important policy means for various countries to promote technological innovation , and has played an important role in rejuvenating the economy and enhancing international competitiveness .
at present , with the rapid development of science and technology and economic globalization , the creation , possession , and use of knowledge and intellectual resources and the quantity and quality of intellectual property rights have become an important foundation for various countries to participate in international competition .
therefore , strengthening international exchanges and cooperation in the protection of intellectual property rights is of great significance to the establishment of a just and rational new international economic order and the promotion of world economic prosperity and development .
the chinese government attaches great importance to protecting intellectual property rights .
in the early period of reform and opening up , china began to establish the intellectual property rights system , and after more than 20 years of efforts , it has formed a relatively complete legal system for intellectual property rights , established a system for protecting intellectual property rights that integrates judicial and administrative law enforcement , and has done a great deal of work in protecting intellectual property rights , thus making important contributions to promoting scientific and technological progress and economic and social development .
as mankind enters the information society in the 21 st century , the scientific and technological revolution will promote the development of the social productive forces with an unprecedented , tremendous motive force .
further improving china 's intellectual property rights system and strengthening international exchanges and cooperation in the protection of intellectual property rights is a requirement for china to open wider to the outside world in the new century , and is also a need for building a socialist modern country and realizing the great rejuvenation of the chinese nation .
we are willing to work together with all countries in the world to establish a fair and rational intellectual property system that is conducive to promoting the scientific and technological and economic development of all countries , and to creating a good environment for all mankind to respect knowledge , advocate science , and protect intellectual property rights .
speeding up the establishment of a mechanism of organization is the most important task facing the sco at present .
