education is the cornerstone of modern civilization .
to improve the quality of the people and enhance the overall national strength , we must vigorously develop the educational cause .
the extensive influence of rural education has a bearing on the overall situation of rural economic and social development .
since the beginning of reform and opening up , tremendous and profound changes have taken place in china 's urban and rural areas , and this is inseparable from the development of education , especially rural education .
the practice of the household contract responsibility system with remuneration linked to output in the rural areas has greatly emancipated the productive forces .
one of the fundamental reasons for the large - scale popularization of advanced and practical agricultural technology , the sudden rise of township and town enterprises , and the large - scale transfer of surplus labor in rural areas to coastal areas and cities and towns is that there are hundreds of millions of rural labor forces who have received compulsory education as the foundation and support , and the great achievements made in the popularization of compulsory education in rural areas have made great contributions .
at present , china 's agriculture and rural economy are at a crucial stage of development , and the development of high - quality , high - efficiency , ecological , and security agriculture , the expansion of agricultural industrialization , and the transfer of surplus labor in rural areas urgently need to comprehensively improve the quality of rural labor force .
the rise of the new scientific and technological revolution in the world and the promotion of the comprehensive building of a comfortably well - off society have set higher demands on the scientific and cultural quality and ideological and moral quality of the vast number of rural population .
without the comprehensive " universal suffrage " in rural areas and without the comprehensive improvement of the quality of peasants , it will be very difficult to achieve a comprehensive well - off life .
we must fully understand the basic , leading , and overall role of rural education in comprehensively building a comfortably well - off society .
