a few days ago , the iraqi interim management committee signed an agreement with the us occupation authorities in baghdad , announcing a step - by - step timetable for the handover of power in iraq by june next year .
the agreement has been endorsed by the international community , and although the eu foreign ministers ' meeting has welcomed it , france believes that " this process is too slow , " and un secretary general annan , while " encouraging " the power transfer plan , said that the " time is not ripe " for the united nations to play a role in iraq , and russia has simply questioned the legitimacy of the agreement .
the iraqi people have turned a cold shoulder , and us public opinion even believes that " this is a major gambling . "
in short , people are mostly semi - confident and wait for a look .
there are many doubts and misgivings in the international community .
this is because people see that the return of political power to iraq is not a willing move of the united states , so it is impossible for the transfer of political power to be thorough , and this is bound to leave a lot of hint .
first , the interim government set up in may next year is not directly elected by the iraqi people , but is elected by the " transitional national congress " elected by 18 provincial - level election committees .
this will be difficult to avoid the suspicion of being controlled by the united states , and its legitimacy may be questioned .
second , the united states has announced that the us military will not withdraw after the handover of power , but will only turn the original " military occupation " into " military presence . "
the us government announced on 18 november that it has decided to impose quotas on three categories of textile products imported from china , namely , knitting , chest clothes , and clothes .
at a time when china is making constant efforts to expand economic and trade cooperation between china and the united states , the us government 's trade protectionism measures cannot but make people deeply regret .
today , with the development of economic globalization , it is extremely inappropriate for the united states to impose new restrictions on china 's textile imports .
first , this kind of abuse of " quota " has restricted the implementation of the wto 's principle of free trade .
on the one hand , he talked about " free trade " in a high - sounding manner , and on the other hand , he frequently sent out " limits " and reerected trade barriers . does this appear to be too arbitrary and unreasonable ?
second , the " quota " has restricted the good development momentum of sino - us economic and trade relations .
since china and the united states reached an agreement on china 's accession to the wto in 1999 , us exports to china have increased by an average annual rate of 15 percent .
from january to september this year , us exports to china increased by 26.2 percent over the same period last year .
in the past two years , us exports of textile raw materials and manufactured goods to china have increased substantially .
as a matter of fact , today 's china has become the fastest growing country in us exports to all countries in the world .
there are many reasons for bush 's failure to achieve his goal during his visit to britain . the most important reason is that after the end of the cold war , the united states has become the only superpower in the world , and it has not taken other people 's eyes and expanded unilateralism .
the united states , without the authorization of the united nations , launched a war against iraq and did not respect the opinions of its major allies on major international issues , such as the reconstruction of iraq .
a recent poll released by the european commission shows that 68 percent of eu citizens believe that the reason for the united states to launch the iraq war is not sufficient , and 53 percent believe that the united states poses a threat to world peace .
second , the united states emphasizes anti - terrorism and wants its allies to invest in it , but does not care about the issues they are concerned about .
with regard to the iraqi reconstruction project , the united states has died at the expense of its own company , and the main contract of the first tender is not willing to be distributed to its own company , the world trade organization has made a ruling on the steel trade dispute , and the united states has imposed high tariffs , and the british industrial and commercial circles have expressed the hope that bush 's visit will make a concession , but in the end , it has not made a clear statement .
third , the united states has put its own values above other countries ' highest standards , and must persist in carrying out democratic transformation of the middle east countries . it has been criticized . some allies have demanded that the united states respect the culture and characteristics of the islamic countries . they believe that one of the reasons for the us military to become bogged down in the quagmire in iraq today is precisely the bitter fruit of its " disrespect . "
