after more than half a year of debate , the japanese self - defense forces ' advance team finally went to iraq before the end of 2003 .
this is the first time that japan has sent troops to overseas battlefields since the end of world war ii .
it reflects japan 's will to become a political and military power , and also marks the beginning of a change in japan 's defense strategy .
the reason why the sdf 's visit has attracted people 's attention is that it is not an isolated incident .
japan has taken advantage of the afghan war to achieve a breakthrough in the self - defense forces ' move out of the country , and has adopted the " emergency legal system " on the korean peninsula , thus laying the groundwork for the self - defense forces to use force or even to gain the initiative , and the koizumi cabinet recently adopted the " basic plan for supporting the reconstruction of iraq " to pave the way for sending troops to iraq .
this step , one step after another , finally broke through the restrictions of japan 's peace constitution and achieved the goal of sending troops overseas .
in addition , japan is also preparing to revise the " concept of basic defense forces " in 2004 in order to legalize and permanently send troops overseas and to set up a non - provisional " permanent force " overseas .
at the same time , under the pretext of the so - called " dprk missile threat , " the japanese cabinet meeting made the decision to start deploying the missile defense system in early 2004 , and introduced the us - made " standard - 3 " and " patriot - 3 " missiles to intercept missiles outside the atmosphere and return to the atmosphere , thus building a dual missile interception network .
it is not difficult to see that the japanese self - defense forces are developing in the direction of a regular army with " both offensive and defensive capabilities , " and the so - called " self - defense forces " that " exclusively defensive " will exist in name only .
the reason why japan 's action has attracted people 's attention is , first of all , that these military decisions have an impact on japan 's peace constitution .
after visiting the yasukuni shrine , koizumi was interviewed by a japanese reporter and defended his action .
his arguments were self - contradictory and full of loopholes .
when asked why koizumi visited the shrine , koizumi replied : " japan 's peace and prosperity are achieved on the basis of the war victims .
my visit is to pray for japan 's peace and prosperity . "
we would like to ask : will koizumi 's so - called " war victims " also include class - a war criminals such as hideki tojo ?
can we say that japan has made the basic contributions of class - a war criminals to the realization of peace and prosperity after the war ?
a reporter asked : why did you choose to visit the yasukuni shrine on 1 january ?
koizumi said that it is japan 's tradition to pay homage to the shrine on the first day of the new year , and many people visited the shrine on that day .
it is understandable that ordinary people pay homage to their relatives and friends , and many family members have clearly indicated that their visit to the yasukuni shrine is only to pay respects to their relatives and friends and to resolutely oppose the worship of class - a war criminals at the yasukuni shrine .
the chinese people are rational , and we have always insisted on separating the japanese people from a small number of militarist elements , separating the ordinary people from the right - wing elements , and paying homage to the yasukuni shrine by ordinary people is not the crux of the historical issue .
