from 4 to 6 january , the 12th summit of the south asian regional cooperation alliance ( south alliance ) , which has been postponed for a whole year , was held in islamabad . the meeting approved the " south asian free trade agreement framework treaty , " the " south asian union 's additional protocol to the convention against terrorism , " and the " south asian social charter , " and announced that all countries of the south african union will work together to develop and cooperate in the economic , cultural , and anti - terrorism fields .
during the south african union summit , the bilateral meeting between indian prime minister vajpayee and pakistani president pervez musharraf was particularly eye - catching .
at the last summit , the handshake between musharraf and vajpayee did not give people too much hope for the development of relations between the two countries .
two years later , due to a series of major measures taken by the two sides , such as the resumption of normal diplomatic relations , army - air transportation links , and the realization of a cease - fire in the kashmir region , indian - pakistani relations have continued to ease and finally achieved the highest - level meeting by taking advantage of the opportunity of the south alliance summit .
in the process of improving bilateral relations , the two countries have taken a big step forward , and regional cooperation in south asia is greeting a new turn for the better .
although indian foreign minister singh said on 4 april that the meeting was a " courtesy , " people believe that the meeting means that indian - pakistani relations will continue to be readjusted in a more positive and pragmatic direction .
the leaders of the two countries have realized that tension and confrontation do not conform to their own national interests , but on the contrary , they have lost the opportunity for economic development .
with the further development of economic globalization , strengthening cooperation and rejuvenating the economy have become the urgent task of the two governments .
although the results of the presidential election held in georgia on the 4 th have not yet been officially announced , the victory of saakashvili , the candidate jointly selected by the right - wing political parties and leader of the national movement party , is a foregone conclusion .
the georgian central election commission announced on the 7 th that more than 95 percent of the voters supported saakashvili according to statistics on 89 percent of the votes .
some heads of state of the commonwealth of independent states also sent congratulatory messages to this young politician .
in fact , saakashvili had announced his victory as early as the night of the election .
he claimed that this result was " the victory of the people , " and indicated that georgia would rapidly take action to open up a new future .
in an interview with the media , many voters said that throwing votes to saakashvili means choosing " new hopes . "
even former president shevardnadze , who was forced to resign , also expressed his support for this former political enemy and praised him for " being young , energetic , and well - educated . "
while placing hopes on saakashvili , people have also noticed that there has been no major change in the situation in georgia in the past two months since president shevardnadze resigned .
it can be said that the newly elected president will still face the old problem .
