the three - party talks on the iraq issue were held at the un headquarters in new york on the 19 th . un secretary general annan held consultations with representatives of the iraqi interim governing council and the us - british coalition interim administration , focusing on how the united nations should play a role in the reconstruction of iraq .
the talks involved political , humanitarian , security , and the appointment of the un special representative in iraq . the three parties frankly exchanged views on this .
at a time when the us - british plan to transfer power in iraq is faced with resistance , whether or not the united nations will and how it will intervene in the reconstruction of iraq will naturally attract people 's attention .
since the united states announced the end of the main war in iraq in early may last year , the situation in iraq has continued to be turbulent , and the attacks against the occupation have occurred one after another , resulting in numerous casualties and no peace in the us - british coalition forces .
former iraqi president saddam was arrested on 13 december last year , but the joy of the united states has not been sustained , the security situation has not improved , and the intensification of the resistance movement has put the occupation authorities in a predicament .
on the other hand , the iraqi people and arab countries unanimously demanded that foreign troops withdraw and return to iraq so that the iraqi people can manage their own country .
at the same time , the united states and britain are striving to reshape the iraqi regime in accordance with their own will and , on this basis , gradually extricate themselves from the quagmire .
for this reason , the method and process of power transfer have become the focus of the current iraq affairs .
the power transfer idea put forward by the us and british management authorities and the iraqi interim governing council in november last year was : the interim iraqi government formed before 1 july this year will be elected by the " transitional national congress , " but the representatives attending the meeting will be selected by the " provincial - level election committee . "
and the shiite faction , which accounts for the majority of the iraqi population , stressed that in order to truly and fairly return to iraq , it is necessary to hold a national direct universal suffrage .
us secretary of state powell 's recent visit to russia is still a focal point of public opinion .
on the one hand , this is because the united states and russia play a decisive role , and their mutual relations have a far - reaching impact on the world today .
more importantly , powell 's visit to moscow has substantive contents and conveyed a clear signal : the dark clouds have appeared in the sky of russian - us relations .
if these dark clouds are not dispersed in a timely manner , the prospects for the relations between the two countries may become dark .
although the channels of dialogue between washington and moscow are very smooth , powell has decided to write an article in the influential russian newspaper , the " news of the elimination , " to explain his position .
in his article , powell pointed out that the united states has been perplexed by a series of incidents in russia 's internal and foreign affairs over the past few months .
he believes that the russian political power has not yet completely accepted the restraints of the law , and the key elements of the civil society , such as freedom of the press and development of political parties , are not firm enough .
russia 's policy toward chechnya and its attitude toward the neighboring countries of the commonwealth of independent states are even more worrying to the united states .
in the eyes of diplomats , using the mass media to make public their positions is the " final way " to communicate information .
the original intention of the united states to make this choice is thought - provoking , and it is obvious that russia is embarrassed and unhappy about this .
after entering the new century , economic globalization has become a major and serious challenge facing african countries .
the leaders of african countries have come to realize more and more clearly that africa should not take advantage of the opportunity to seek countermeasures .
on 9 july 2002 , the african union was formally established and started operation . since then , the african countries have actively promoted the " new partnership for african development " , worked hard to develop the economy , and tried to get rid of the unfavorable situation in economic globalization as soon as possible . on the other hand , they have made great efforts to resolve the main obstacle to the great cause of african rejuvenation - - the issue of armed conflicts , so as to create a united , peaceful , and stable environment .
at present , the overall situation in africa has become more relaxed , the hot - point issue has been significantly lowered , and all countries have strengthened their sense of urgency to end armed conflicts .
with the strong support of the united nations and the international community , the influential regional organizations , regional powers , and well - known politicians in africa have actively taken action to intensify their efforts to resolve regional conflicts and eliminate internal strife , and some conflicts and turbulence that have lasted for many years have basically been brought under control .
for example , the congo ( drc ) set up a national unity government in june last year , the government of sao tome and principe in july , the government of liberia and the rebel forces signed a peace agreement in the ghanaian capital of akla in august , the sudanese government and the rebel forces in the southern part of the country in september , and the armed and political factions in somalia started peace talks in kenya in october to discuss the national peace process , and the burundi government signed a peace agreement with the rebels in november .
of course , the current situation of stability in the african region is still relatively weak , the results of peace still need to be consolidated , and some potential or practical armed conflicts still need to be resolved .
at the same time , there is still a big gap between the economic growth rate of african countries and the developing countries in asia and other regions , and these are all unfavorable factors for africa 's development .
how african countries can effectively cope with the challenge of economic globalization and realize their dream of rejuvenation still requires the african people to make long - term and arduous efforts .
