all localities and departments concerned should take emergency action and go all out to prevent the spread of the epidemic in accordance with the arrangements of the party central committee and the state council .
at present , the work of preventing and controlling avian flu in the whole country is being carried out in an intense and orderly manner .
the highly pathogenic avian flu is a kind of animal epidemic that has spread rapidly and has seriously endangered the production of animal husbandry and seriously endangered the health and safety of the masses .
conscientiously doing a good job in the prevention and control of the highly pathogenic avian flu has a bearing on the health and safety of the masses , on the development of agriculture and the increase of peasants ' income , on the overall situation of economic development , and on social stability . all localities and departments should take the important thinking of " three represents " as the guide , strengthen leadership and close cooperation in accordance with the requirements of the " law of the people 's republic of china on the prevention and control of animal diseases ,
as the world 's largest debtor , the amount of us foreign debt is increasing again .
the u.s. debt to foreign creditors totaled 6.494 trillion u.s. dollars at the end of september , an increase of 2.2 percent over the previous figure , the treasury department said today .
on average , each american has already paid over $ 20,000 in foreign debt .
it is a coincidence that a week ago , the international monetary fund [ imf ] issued a research report system , which sharply sounded the alarm for the shaken financial foundation of the united states , and pointed out that the us foreign debt , which has constantly broken through the record , has reached the level of threatening global financial stability .
statistics show that foreign private investors have controlled about 40 percent of us government bonds .
in the first half of the 20 th century , it is unavoidable for people to think of the strategy of president roosevelt : adopting a deficit policy to stimulate the economy within the country , while the fiscal deficit is resolved through foreign debt .
this move has indeed played an important role in stimulating " effective demand " and resolving the urgent needs of the economic crisis .
however , people can see that many us administrations tend to take this as a " magic drug . "
however , since president reagan initiated a tax cut and arms expansion in the 1980 s , the us financial deficit has gradually increased and has finally become the largest debtor country .
the first round of six - party talks is an important step in the process of peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue on the korean peninsula .
some common points formed by various parties during the talks have laid the necessary foundation for continuing the talks and further clarified the objectives , channels , and principles for resolving the nuclear issue on the korean peninsula .
in the past few months , all parties concerned have insisted on peacefully resolving the nuclear issue on the peninsula through dialogue , and on the basis of the results of the first round of six - party talks , they have extensively carried out coordination and consultations at different levels and made unremitting efforts to hold the second round of talks as soon as possible .
at the same time , the dprk and the united states have further demonstrated varying degrees of flexibility .
at present , important progress has been made in the preparatory work for the talks , and the good talks have been well received by the people .
the results of the second round of six - party talks and whether the peace process can be maintained are of common concern to all parties concerned and the international community .
in this regard , a spokesman for the chinese foreign ministry said that the goal of the six - party talks is to maintain and promote the process of peaceful settlement through dialogue , and we are willing to make joint efforts with all parties concerned in this regard .
the basic starting point of the chinese side is to safeguard peace and stability on the korean peninsula and realize a nuclear - free peninsula .
the chinese side believes that so long as all parties attending the meeting uphold the sincerity of peace talks , respect each other , and hold consultations on an equal footing , they will be able to create favorable conditions for promoting the settlement of relevant issues .
at the end of the 1970 s , the relations between the two countries deteriorated , and the two countries severed diplomatic ties in 1981 .
us president reagan once listed a long string of crimes for libya 's leader qazi , such as accusing libya of secretly developing nuclear weapons , engaging in military intervention and terrorism , etc.
the two sides had a battle of words , and the united states launched two surgical strikes against libya , namely , the " agni " and the " golden valley . "
since then , the united states has imposed economic sanctions against libya , political strikes , diplomatic containment , and military threats .
qazi , under heavy pressure , did not give in .
at present , the warming - up of relations between murray has been attributed to the deterrent effect of the iraq war , which seems to be biased .
as a matter of fact , for many years , the unique character of qazi , on the one hand , opposed the united states , and on the other hand , he has always dished out an olive branch to the united states , but unfortunately , he has not received any response .
after the end of the iraq war , the various parties in the middle east have readjusted their strategic and regional forces , and this has provided an opportunity for the resumption of the diplomatic relations between the two countries .
as far as qazi is concerned , repairing relations with the united states can end the sanctions , revitalize the economy , improve the people 's livelihood , extricate himself from an isolated situation , and merge with the international community .
by giving up those things that have not yet been achieved and cannot be achieved for the time being , we can exchange for a new environment in which there is a way out for another village .
from 7 to 8 february , political figures from europe , the united states , and other regions of the world gathered in munich , germany , to attend the 40 th munich security policy conference .
the so - called " munich security policy conference " is an international security forum founded by non - governmental personages in germany and sponsored by the german government . in recent years , especially after the " 11 september " incident , people have increasingly attached importance to it , and has been called the " davos forum " in the security field .
an important topic of the meeting was cross - atlantic relations .
the remarks made by the european and us political leaders at the meeting show that the two sides are making every effort to shake off the shadow of the iraq war and to return to the track of cooperation .
bertrm , director of the berlin institute of international and security affairs , said that this is a meeting for the restoration of relations between europe and the united states , and both sides have the desire to move closer to each other .
as far as european - us relations are concerned , the new information sent out by the meeting is that europe and the united states need to resume dialogue , seriously consider the common tasks facing both sides , and find the interests needed to fulfill these common tasks .
compared with last year 's meeting , the smell of gunpowder in this year 's meeting has disappeared , and the positions of the two sides are approaching .
although the " old europe " represented by france and germany is still deeply rooted in the us war on iraq , it said that it would " look forward to the future . "
german foreign minister fischer said at the meeting : " although we have different views on the war , we must work together to ensure the realization of peace after the war in iraq , and we must look forward to this .
he also said that although germany will not send troops to iraq , germany will not obstruct nato from playing a direct role in iraq .
the united states , which has taken the initiative in the field of modern media , has monopolized a large number of international news - speaking rights , and its public opinion propaganda has long spread all over the world , and it has simply reached an all - embracing level . why does it still have to spend a huge amount of money to set up satellite television stations that cover 22 countries in the middle east ?
in the words of the responsible person of the " freedom no . 1 " television station , it is necessary to provide a " comprehensive and just " news platform for arab countries .
however , some analysts pointed out that " freedom no . 1 " will be a strategic weapon for the united states to carry out public opinion infiltration , cultural invasion , and attacks on arab countries , and an important propaganda tool for the united states to carry out the policy of integrating the middle east and transforming the islamic world .
this shows that the mission of " freedom no . 1 " is an extraordinary one , and there are three major candidates to be selected : first , to spread the " concept of freedom . "
the united states believes that the islamic civilization is a serious obstacle to the promotion of modern civilization by the west , and the extremist religious forces in the middle east islamic countries are a breeding ground for international terrorism with anti - us as the main characteristics . in order to effectively counter terrorism , it is necessary to transform the islamic world , so that it can recognize and accept the western value concept , way of life , and political system .
the united states is trying to instill its own ideology into the arabs through the imperceptible influence of the " freedom no . 1 " program .
second , the united states should improve its image .
the united states pursues unilateralism toward the outside world and acts as it pleases on a series of international issues . its hegemonic acts have made the arab countries and the islamic world .
after the " 11 september " incident , the contradictions between the united states , which has always been biased toward israel , and the islamic world in the middle east have become increasingly acute .
the us occupation of iraq by force under the pretext of eliminating weapons of mass destruction and anti - terrorism without solid evidence and un authorization has aroused strong resentment among the muslims .
the talks between pakistani and indian officials were held in islamabad from 16 to 18 february , with the hope of peace rising again on the south asian continent .
officials of the two countries have decided on the agenda and mode of future talks and established a mechanism for continuing dialogue . this move indicates that the pakistan - india dialogue process has been resumed after two years of suspension , and has laid a foundation for the two countries to gradually resolve all outstanding issues , including the kashmir dispute , and has embodied the valuable peace sincerity of the two sides .
prior to the talks , although the relations between the two countries have been warming up by a series of good - will moves by the two sides , most analysts still hold a cautious attitude toward the prospects of the peace process .
it is no wonder that looking back at the sudden ups and downs in the relations between pakistan and india in recent years , it seems that no one will dare to guarantee : today , the sun is still on the negotiating table , and tomorrow will not become a lightning on the border .
however , the statement of the two countries , read with a smiling face by the pakistani foreign minister , has once again filled the optimistic mood , and has given the eyes of many people who have been concerned about the situation in south asia for a long time .
first of all , the timetable set for the talks is very workable , and the two sides have not only specified the specific time and topics of the talks , but also set different levels of talks according to the degree of importance of the topics to be discussed .
second , the two sides have drawn lessons from the failure of the talks between the leaders of the two countries during the summit in july 2001 , and adopted the method of " step - by - step " dialogue , so that the level of the talks will be reduced from a low level to a high level , so as to make full preparations for high - level dialogue .
third , after experiencing bilateral relations , the two countries unanimously agreed that war is not a good way to resolve disputes . the two sides should be far away from war , and this consensus has laid a foundation for the leaders of the two countries to reach an understanding that " pakistan and india will never fight any more . "
to comprehensively and accurately understand and implement the principle of " one country , two systems , " it is necessary to integrate " one country " with " two systems , " " patriotism , " and " love for hong kong , " integrate the respect for hong kong 's high degree of autonomy with the maintenance of state sovereignty , and integrate the maintenance of hong kong 's capitalism with the maintenance of socialism in the main body of the country .
only in this way can we effectively safeguard the well - being of hong kong compatriots and conform to the long - term interests of the country and the entire people .
since hong kong 's return to the motherland , the central government has unswervingly implemented the principle of " one country , two systems " and handled affairs in strict accordance with the basic law .
the vast number of hong kong compatriots enjoy unprecedented democratic rights as masters of their own affairs .
with the strong support of the central government and the mainland of the motherland , hong kong has overcome various risks and challenges , such as the impact of the asian financial crisis , and has continued to maintain its status as an international financial , trade , and shipping center .
practice has proven that the principle of " one country , two systems " has great vitality .
today , the speech made by comrade deng xiaoping 20 years ago has once again declared to the world the firm determination of the central authorities to implement the principle of " one country , two systems " and , more importantly , to enable everyone to comprehensively and accurately understand the principle of " one country , two systems " and constantly push forward the great practice of " one country , two systems . "
