after the " 9.11 " incident , us president bush dished out the " preemptive " strategy in june 2002 , put it into practice in us foreign relations , and fought the first " preemptive " war in iraq in march last year .
the concept of " preemptive strikes " not only runs counter to the norms of international law with " mutual respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity " as the core , but also will inevitably trigger a dangerous effect of mass follow , and a new situation of turbulence will emerge in the international order .
at the beginning of the " preemptive " theory , some political figures in the united states raised this question : " if other countries follow the example one after another , what should they do ? "
as a result , over the past two years , more and more countries have claimed to be " preemptive " and the " preemptive " forces are expanding .
this is a new trend worthy of attention and research .
in the same month when bush put forward the " preemptive " strategy , australian prime minister howard was the first to come out to express his support .
he said that once the relevant terrorists receive reliable intelligence to attack australia , australia will adopt a " preemptive " strategy and will not hesitate to take military action against neighboring countries .
he even suggested that the principle of " preemptive strikes " be written into the un charter , holding that it is necessary to amend the un charter and give all countries the right to " gain the initiative " in order to strike at terrorists or countries that support terrorist activities .
in northeast asia , as early as in the " defense white paper " published in july 1999 , the japanese defense agency proposed that before facing missile attacks or military invasion , japan could launch " preemptive " attacks on foreign bases .
after the iraq war , the call of japan for " preemptive " strategy was even more rampant .
recently , international opinion has made many comments on the current us policy toward africa .
the " foreign policy focus " published by the united states in january this year is entitled " the prospects of africa policy in 2004 . " the article holds that in the past year , the bush administration 's foreign policy has directly or indirectly had a negative impact on africa . in particular , the united states has paid full attention to the issue of the war against terrorism and the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction . in particular , the united states has been greatly scattered in iraq .
people still remember that in order to show concern for africa , the bush administration formulated the " president 's emergency plan for the treatment of aids " in january last year , and promised to provide at least $ 3 billion in funds to africa every year .
in july last year , president bush visited five african countries , including senegal , south africa , botswana , uganda , and nigeria , and promised to provide 15 billion us dollars of aid to african countries in the prevention and treatment of aids , and another 100 million us dollars was used to fight against african terrorist activities , and announced the food emergency aid program and educational aid program .
these aid programs were once welcomed by african countries , and have won many praise internationally .
however , one year has passed and the concrete actions of the united states have yet to be implemented .
africa is in urgent need of assistance .
after entering the new century , africa is faced with all kinds of development challenges . in order to achieve the " development goals of the century " set by the united nations in 2000 , to strive to reduce hunger and poverty , and to promote health and education , africa has set up a " african union " to coordinate the affairs of the whole continent , and has drawn up a " new partnership plan for african development " aimed at promoting the development of various countries . however , due to the weak economic foundation , the development fund has always been very short .
the united nations has repeatedly called on developed countries to use 0.7 percent of their gross domestic product for official aid to the least developed countries .
however , the united states ' official aid accounts for only 0.1 percent of its gross domestic product ( gdp ) , which is far short of the united nations ' demand , and ranks the last in the list of donor countries .
recently , european public opinion has been discussing a hot topic : whether the " three magnates " meeting between german chancellor schroeder , french president chirac , and british prime minister blair is gradually moving toward a mechanism .
public opinion calls germany , france , and britain the " new three giants " of the european union , and the relations among the three countries are called the " new triangle . "
the " new triangle " is a new thing . no matter which angle it is still to be observed , it seems that the " new triangle " will be conducive to the process of european integration , and this will help europe play an important role in the international arena as a pole in the multipolar world .
taking a general look at the history of europe over the past 100 years , a basic characteristic of the relationship between germany , france , and britain in the triangle is that the united kingdom and france are united , constraining or resisting germany .
two world wars are proof of this .
during the cold war , the east and west germany were suppressed in the warsaw pact and nato respectively .
after the end of the cold war , germany has become more powerful , the pattern of western european forces has become more unbalanced , and france has become more suspicious . as a result , the " axis of germany and france " has been out of order for a time , and the united states and britain have once again been close to each other , and its intention is still to contain germany .
however , in recent years , with the reactivate of the " axis of germany and france " and the fierce collision between unipolar and multipolar world concepts , the eu has been seriously divided on the iraq issue .
the " old europe " represented by germany and france is completely contrary to the " new europe " represented by britain and poland on the iraq war issue .
this split also happened to be the largest expansion in the history of the european union .
egyptian president mubarak made a speech on the reform of arab countries in cairo a few days ago , criticizing the outside world 's practice of imposing a single reform model on arab countries , and warning that such an attempt can only be just the opposite , and will not benefit the security and stability of the middle east region .
he believes that the reform measures should be based on their own characteristics and according to their capability , while the single reform mode has ignored the cultural background , social customs , and religious characteristics of different countries .
at the same time , he pointed out that the arab countries welcome foreign assistance in the course of reform , but such efforts should clearly understand the different national conditions and respect the wishes of various countries , so as to promote the political , economic , and cultural reform process of the arab countries .
the egyptian leader 's remarks represent the common view of the arab countries .
at present , under the pressure of anti - terrorism , anti - proliferation , and democratic reform , the middle east , as one of the world 's hot spots , is deliberating on new turbulence and will lead to new integration .
after the two wars in afghanistan and iraq , how did iraq , which was regarded by the united states as one of the " axis of evil , " carry out political reconstruction ?
how will various political systems and social models in the middle east region evolve ?
this is not only a concern of the arab world and the international community , but also an interest of the united states and its western allies .
after meeting with visiting bahrain crown prince sahman in washington on 9 april , us secretary of state powell reiterated that the united states would pursue a " western - style democratic and capitalist plan " in iraq and the middle east .
he also stressed : " we are considering what we can do and how to institutionalize this . "
last year , it was the " cultural and educational year " defined by the international olympic committee .
