in recent years , the issue of small weapons has been closely watched by the international community .
this shows that all sides have become increasingly aware of the harm caused by the excessive accumulation and illegal trafficking of small weapons to the stability , post - war reconstruction , and social development of the relevant regions and countries .
fortunately , the united nations has taken a series of effective actions to resolve this issue .
in 2001 , the " gun protocol " attached to the " un convention on cracking down on transnational organized crime " and the " program of action " of the united nations for small weapons were reached one after another .
this has provided a legal and policy basis for the proper resolution of the small arms issue , and has demonstrated the international community 's determination to crack down on the illegal trade of small weapons .
in the past three years , the international community has made great progress in promoting the implementation of the " gun protocol " and the implementation of the " program of action . " in particular , the successful convening of the first annual meeting of the united nations on small weapons in 2003 has provided a new motive force for the continued comprehensive and effective implementation of the " program of action . "
the resolution no. 58 / 241 adopted by the un general assembly decided to set up a working group to negotiate on the identification and tracing of international documents on illegal small weapons , which will undoubtedly further promote the international community 's efforts to crack down on the illegal trade of small weapons .
similarly , the security council has also paid more and more attention to the issue of small weapons , and has conducted special deliberations on many occasions , and adopted the chairman 's statement and resolution .
moreover , when examining a series of issues concerning the protection of civilians , women , and children in conflicts , the security council stressed the importance of handling the issue of small weapons .
