promoting economic development and striving to eliminate poverty is the only way for developing countries to move toward sustainable development .
without solving the problem of poverty in the developing countries , the development of the developed countries will also be difficult to sustain .
rational use of resources and protection of the environment is an inevitable requirement for achieving sustainable development .
development cannot be carried out at the cost of wasting resources and sacrificing the environment .
natural resources are not inexhaustible , but the demand for the development of human society is constantly growing . if the relations between the two sides are not handled properly , it will inevitably lead to the deterioration of the ecological environment and seriously threaten the survival and development of mankind .
only by following the path of recycling economy based on the most effective use of resources and environmental protection can we achieve sustained development .
realizing all - round social progress and improving the people 's living standards and quality are the ultimate goal of sustainable development .
