( international ) us flu spread to peak
xinhua news agency report of december 31 from los angeles ( by staff reporter yan liang ) - the us center for disease control and prevention said on the 31 st that the united states has reached its peak in the past 30 - plus years , with 45 of the 50 states in the united states having a relatively large area of flu spreading , and the number of deaths caused by influenza rapidly increasing .
according to statistics released by the center as of december 20 , the number of deaths caused by influenza in the united states has reached a record high of 7.8 percent of all deaths in the same period .
at least 42 children died of influenza in the united states , and the number of adult deaths is also on the rise , but it is still impossible to accurately calculate the number of deaths .
experts believe that there are two reasons for the serious spread of influenza in 2003 : first , the flu virus is not the " panama - type " flu virus , which was popular in previous years , which has made it impossible to effectively prevent the virus , and second , the united states had a surplus of influenza vaccines last year , and the two major supply companies have reduced the output of the vaccines to 83 million this year , resulting in the shortage of vaccines this year .
although an average of 36,000 people in the united states die of influenza every year and 114,000 people are hospitalized due to flu , it is still very rare to see a certain degree of social panic like this flu .
william thompson , an epidemic expert in the united states , believes that this flu is the most serious in the united states in the past 30 years and more , and it is even earlier than in previous years . in many schools , there has been a large - scale spread of flu , and many places where flu vaccines have been vaccinated have been formed .
in the face of such a grim situation , the us department of health activated the emergency handling center on 19 december and sent medical experts groups to various states .
three killed in traffic accident in zhejiang
xinhua news agency , hangzhou , january 1 ( fang li and zhang hongming ) a serious traffic accident occurred in ninghai county , zhejiang province on the early morning of the 1 st .
due to the heavy fog , an overloaded car and a large truck collided , killing three people and injuring four .
at about 2 : 00 a.m . on the 1 st , the driver , hua , drove a red flag taxi with a license number of zhejiang 's bot 8705 , from linhai to ninghai , carrying six passengers on board .
at that time , the road was filled with fog and the sight was not clear .
when the two sides reached a distance of 700 meters , the taxi and a large truck carrying the same direction collided with each other .
it has been learned that at that time , the large truck entered the main lane from the super lane , and the taxi was unable to avoid the accident , and the car crashed into the bottom of the truck . the vehicle was seriously distorted , and three of the seven people , including the driver , were killed on the spot .
after the accident , the traffic police department of zhejiang province promptly issued a circular calling on the traffic police departments of the whole province to take immediate measures to strengthen traffic management under bad weather conditions , prevent the overloading and speeding of vehicles from causing accidents , and ensure road safety during the spring festival transportation period .
( international ) another 14 survivors rescued in iran
xinhua news agency , tehran , january 1 , iran 's national radio said on the 1st that the iranian search and rescue personnel found another 14 survivors on the 31 st and the 1 st in the ruins of the basam earthquake - stricken area .
" we have saved at least one life , " said ali ashtra , a staff member of the iranian red crescent society , when he rescued a young shop owner from his clothes on the 1st .
i have gone to the battlefield and experienced many tests , but i have never been so happy . "
the iranian national radio said that the search and rescue personnel also rescued a nine - year - old girl and a pregnant woman from the ruins .
their health is very weak .
according to the state radio , rescue personnel found 11 survivors on the 31 st , including a four - month - old baby and an 80 - year - old woman .
however , rescue personnel believe that with the passage of time , the chance of finding survivors is very slim .
according to statistics , the search and rescue personnel have found about 28,000 bodies at the scene of the earthquake and have buried some of the bodies .
in addition , they rescued 2,000 survivors from the ruins , most of whom were found the next day of the earthquake .
according to the latest report released by the un humanitarian coordination office on the 31 st , the death toll in the earthquake - stricken areas and other channels in iran is expected to rise to 34,000 .
