( international ) us rescue team says aid to iran has no political color
xinhua news agency , bakam , iran , january 2 ( reporter jiang xiaofeng , liao zhenyun ) - the head of the us international development agency 's humanitarian aid project , steve kartlin , who is taking part in the earthquake relief work in iran 's bakan region , told xinhua reporters on the 2 nd that the us rescue team 's participation in the rescue activities in iran does not have any political color .
kartlin pointed out that the us organization of this rescue team " has nothing to do with politics , " and the us had provided similar humanitarian aid to iran in the past .
he said that the rescue team , composed of 84 people , had set up a city search and rescue team and a battlefield hospital in the bakan area , and several other teams were responsible for assessing the damage of the houses in the city .
they also brought with them plastic sheeting , tents , and other relief materials .
when asked how long the us rescue team will stay in bakan , karterin said : " how long will the owner ( the iranian government ) stay ? "
kartlin also said that the activities of the us rescue team in bakan were free , and there was no iranian police to protect or track them .
in addition , he believes that the iranian government 's ability to respond to and deal with the earthquake is " first - rate and outstanding . "
the us international development agency is a subsidiary of the international development and cooperation agency and is under the administration of the us state department .
since the united states and iran severed diplomatic relations in 1980 , the two sides have never resumed normal relations .
so far , the united states still regards iran as one of the " countries that support terrorism " and one of the " axis of evil . "
the us dispatch of a rescue team to iran this time was an action taken at the invitation of the iranian ambassador to the united nations .
( international ) israeli deputy prime minister denies plans to expand golan heights settlements
xinhua news agency , london , january 2 , israeli deputy prime minister olmert denied on the 2 nd that israel plans to expand jewish settlements in the golan heights , saying that there is no such " plan " or such " policy . "
israeli agriculture minister qazi told the press on december 31 last year that the israeli government plans to double the number of jewish settlers living in the golan heights before a peace dialogue with syria , so as to strengthen control over the golan heights .
in an interview with bbc , olmert said that the development of agriculture , tourism , and settlements on the golan heights as mentioned by qazi was wrong .
he said : " in the past two days , i have repeatedly verified with the premier and the finance minister , and in accordance with the government 's commitment , there is no such approved plan . "
he said that although some ministers agreed to such plans , the government would not give them any support .
the golan heights was seized from syria in the third middle east war in 1967 , with a total of 17,000 jewish settlers .
because of this , syria and israel have been in a state of war for a long time .
qazi 's statement on the expansion of the golan heights immediately aroused widespread concern in the international community , and syria condemned israel 's expansion plan , stressing that it was illegal .
china 's high - tech modern weapons industry has begun to take shape
xinhua news agency , beijing , january 3 ( reporter li jinyan and li bin ) in the past year , the china ordnance group corporation , as one of the top 10 military industrial enterprises in china , has made major progress in the development and reform of new and high - tech weapons and equipment .
ma zhigeng , general manager of the china ordnance group corporation , said here on 3 march that the company 's sales income in 2003 was 49.7 billion yuan , an increase of 19.7 percent over the same period of last year , and the whole system was able to turn losses into profits two years ahead of schedule , and the high - tech modern weapons industry has already taken shape in china .
the ordnance industry is the largest industry in the field of science , technology , and industry for national defense , and has a basic strategic position in the modernization of national defense .
in recent years , the china ordnance group corporation has persistently taken the lead in the development of science and technology and qualified personnel . on the one hand , it has paid attention to the development of high - tech weapons , and on the other hand , it has successfully developed a number of high - tech weapons and equipment urgently needed by the chinese armed forces , and has developed a number of high - tech military products .
at the same time , the china ordnance group corporation has made great efforts to push forward structural readjustment , and the total number of 21 enterprises has been declared bankrupt and closed down . the total number of staff members and workers has been reduced from 660,000 when the group company was formed to 360,000 , with a net reduction of 116,000 people , and six enterprises have been reorganized and listed on the stock market .
( international ) mongolian animal husbandry situation improves in 2003
xinhua news agency , ulan bator , january 5 ( reporter lu guodong ) according to local media reports on the 5 th , by the end of 2003 , mongolia 's livestock reserves had reached 2530.78 million , an increase of 162.33 million over the same period last year .
this is the first time that mongolia 's livestock reserves have picked up after three consecutive years of decline .
last summer , there was plenty of rainfall , and there was no snow in spring and winter , thus creating favorable conditions for the improvement of the livestock industry in mongolia .
by the end of 2003 , there were a total of 255.56 million camel , 195.83 million horse , 178.43 million cattle , 107.062 million sheep , and 106.34 million sheep .
compared with the same period last year , the number of camel , sheep , and sheep has increased , while the number of horses and cattle has decreased .
mongolia 's livestock industry was basically privatization in the 1990 s .
however , after privatization , the livestock industry was completely " dependent on heaven . "
from 1994 to 1999 , mongolia 's livestock industry has been thriving for six years in a row due to the smooth wind and rain .
at the end of 1999 , mongolia 's livestock reserves reached a record high of 33.5 million .
however , from 2000 to 2002 , there have been three consecutive years of heavy snow and summer drought , and mongolia 's livestock industry has also suffered setbacks for three years in a row .
at the end of 2002 , the number of domestic animals in mongolia was only 236.85 million , a drop of 98.55 million in three years .
