( international ) us dollar hits new low
xinhua news agency , new york , january 8 , under the influence of a speech by the president of the european central bank , the us dollar again fell to a low ebb eight days after a flash in the pan on the 7 th .
the president of the european central bank , jean - claude trichet , issued a commentary on the same day , saying that the excessively high euro exchange rate has had a negative impact on the export of european enterprises , but he believes that the gradual recovery of the world economy and the rebound in consumer demand have partially offset the impact of the appreciation of the euro .
at the same time , he pointed out that the strong euro also played a positive role in the price stability of the euro zone to a certain extent , so the european central bank decided to maintain the original interest rate level .
investors regard the comments as a signal that officials of the euro zone are not worried about the appreciation of the euro , which has led to a drop in the exchange rate of the us dollar against other major currencies in the west , and the exchange rate of the pound against the us dollar has risen to a new high in 11 years .
at the closing session of the new york foreign exchange , the exchange rate of the euro against the us dollar dropped from 1.2640 to 1.2761 , the exchange rate of the british pound against the us dollar from 1.8180 to 1.8320 , and the exchange rate of the us dollar against the japanese yen fell from 106.27 to 106.17 , and the exchange rate of the us dollar against the swiss francs dropped from 1.2398 to 1.2867 .
