( archaeological discoveries ) 31 qin tombs discovered in fengxiang county , shaanxi
xinhua news agency , xi ' an , january 15 ( reporter : iron ma ) - in the past , the historical circles have all along believed that the palace of the nantou village in fengxiang county , baoji city , shaanxi province , has become a place for the royal family to carry out major worship activities after the qin people moved to the yongdu city . however , the shaanxi archaeological research institute recently discovered 31 qin tombs in this palace .
in order to coordinate with a company in baoji city to build a plant at the site , the shaanxi archaeological research institute carried out archaeological exploration in this area , and discovered a total of 31 qin tombs in the western zhou and spring and autumn periods within an area of about 20,000 square meters .
through the clean - up and excavation of these ancient tombs by the yongcheng archaeological team of shaanxi province , more than 40,000 cultural relics , such as bronze ware and clay , were unearthed .
one of the qin tomb is a two - coffin with a two - horse burial pit next to the tomb .
a total of 15 pieces of bronze ware and utensils were unearthed in the tomb , and the bronze medallion , pot , and hammer were unearthed .
among them , the fine bronze medallion has been produced , with a very exquisite tattoo , and has maintained the style of the western zhou dynasty 's bronze ware casting .
from the items that were buried together , we can see that the owner of the tomb was the qin nobles in the late zhou dynasty .
experts guess that there should be a huge ancient tombs nearby .
this accident found that it was of great historical value to study the relocation of the qin capital and the layout of the yongcheng city during the qin dynasty .
tian yaqi , deputy research fellow of the shaanxi provincial archaeological research institute and head of the yongcheng archaeological team , said : in the past , the historical circles have always believed that the palace of the nantou village was a place for the royal family to carry out major worship activities in the qin dynasty and the western han dynasty .
this time , the discovery shows that before the relocation of the city of yongyong , this place was a fencer of the western zhou dynasty and had experienced several ups and downs .
