china takes measures to prevent entry of foot - and - mouth disease in tajikistan
xinhua news agency , beijing , january 15 ( reporter du yu ) the ministry of agriculture and the state administration of quality supervision , inspection , and quarantine jointly issued a public notice a few days ago , banning the import of hoofed animals and their products directly or indirectly from tajikistan , and those that have arrived at china 's ports will be returned or destroyed .
according to a report by the world animal health organization , three cases of foot - and - mouth disease have occurred in tajikistan recently .
in order to protect the safety of china 's livestock industry , the ministry of agriculture and the state administration of quality supervision , inspection , and quarantine also issued a public notice , urging the prohibition of the import of clogged animals and their products from tajikistan by mail or passengers .
once discovered , all the cases will be returned or destroyed .
international navigation vessels , aircraft , trains , and other transport vehicles that pass through china or stay in china , if they discover that there are birds and their products from the republic of korea , they will be sealed up , and their waste , sore , and so on will be dealt with without harm under the supervision of the entry - exit inspection and quarantine organization and shall not be abandoned without authorization .
the circular calls for the destruction of hoofed animals and their products from tajikistan , which were intercepted by the customs and border defense departments , under the supervision of the entry - exit inspection and quarantine organs .
( international ) air passenger company 's volume exceeded boeing for the first time last year
xinhua news agency , paris , january 15 ( reporter xu zhenqiang ) the european airbus corporation issued a statement on the 15 th , saying that the company 's aircraft delivery volume in 2003 was 305 , which exceeded the original estimate of 300 , and was the first to lead its competitor , the us boeing company , and ranked first in the world .
last year , the number of aircraft delivered by the air passenger company was slightly higher than that of 303 in 2002 .
the company forecasts that the market will remain sluggish this year , so the volume of its aircraft will be " close to 300 . "
the us boeing company announced earlier this month that its aircraft delivery volume last year was 281 , and is expected to be between 275 and 290 this year .
in 2003 , the number of aircraft paid by the air cargo company rose to 52 percent of the world 's total , and in 2001 and 2002 , its global share was 38 percent and 44 percent respectively .
last year , the company received 284 orders from its customers , with a total value of 32.8 billion us dollars , and the actual number of orders that were cancelled in the middle of the year was 254 , accounting for 52 percent of the world 's total .
the senior management of the european air defense and space company , which owns 80 percent of the shares of the company , said that they do not expect the civil aircraft market to recover quickly , but hope that the company will maintain the current level of delivery of aircraft by 2005 .
