( international ) silicon valley unemployment rate falls , forecasts recovery of us high - tech industry
xinhua news agency , los angeles , january 19 ( reporter yan liang ) an influential economic development research institute in the silicon valley in the united states recently published a report saying that the unemployment rate in silicon valley is declining rapidly .
this is a clear signal that high - tech industries in the region have begun to recover .
in its annual report " silicon valley 2004 economic index , " the non - profit - making organization " joint venture silicon valley " said that the unemployment rate in the silicon valley between the second quarter of 2002 and the second quarter of 2003 decreased from 10% in the previous year to 5% .
the report said that with the gradual recovery of high - tech industries , the unemployment rate will continue to decline .
the challenge facing the economic development of silicon valley at present is the need for a large number of well - trained high - tech workers to fill new jobs in the future .
the report said that among the various high - tech industries in silicon valley , the unemployment rate of the biotechnology industry is the lowest , and the recovery momentum is also the most obvious , and the number of risk investment in the silicon valley 's biotechnology industry in 2003 is the same as that of the computer software industry for the first time .
the report said the biotechnology industry will play an increasingly important role in the economic development of silicon valley .
the report also showed that the average salary of employees in silicon valley dropped for the third consecutive year from the second quarter of 2002 to the second quarter of 2003 , but the decline has dropped from 6 percent in the previous year to 1.5 percent .
silicon valley is still a rich region in the united states , with an average annual salary of 624,000 us dollars , 60 percent higher than the national average .
however , the consumption level in this region is 47 percent higher than that of the whole country .
