( international ) economists predict us dollar devaluation as the biggest winner
xinhua news agency , davos , switzerland , january 23 ( reporter li jie and ding xigang ) the 34 th annual meeting of the world economic forum , which is being held in davos , switzerland , held a special discussion on the issue of the trend of us dollar devaluation on the 23 rd . some experts predict that the united states will be the biggest winner in the continuous decline of the us dollar exchange rate .
most economists attending the meeting held that us officials , including us treasury secretary john snow , seem to have abandoned the " strong us dollar policy " pursued in recent years .
the us dollar 's low exchange rate will provide greater space for economic development and more job opportunities for the united states , which is very obvious in the manufacturing industry .
at the same time , the devaluation of the us dollar has made us products more competitive in the domestic and foreign markets , which will help the united states fill its trade deficit .
however , experts believe that a weak dollar will also have an adverse impact on the united states .
first , the us stock market may continue to be sluggish , the value of all kinds of investment will drop , and foreign investors will withdraw their funds because of the further decline of the us dollar , and second , the increasing value of imports will eventually lead to a decline in the living standards of the americans , and third , the sharp devaluation of the us dollar may also lead to trade and financial turbulence .
however , the devaluation of the us dollar has dealt a more serious blow to europe , japan , and canada .
the european economy is facing the danger of a full - scale recession following a drop in the u.s. dollar .
