( international ) japanese imports and exports both reach record high in 2003
xinhua news agency , tokyo , january 26 ( reporter le shaoyan ) according to statistics released by the japanese finance ministry on the 26 th , japan 's import and export trade volume in 2003 reached a record high , and the trade surplus again broke through 10 trillion yen in three years .
in terms of exports , japan 's exports to the united states dropped 9.8 percent from the previous year , but exports to asia increased by 12.9 percent .
this not only made up for the decrease in japan 's exports to the united states , but also enabled japan 's total exports to increase by 4.7 percent over the previous year , reaching a record high of 54.589 trillion yen .
with regard to imports , japan 's total imports in 2003 increased by 5 percent over the previous year , reaching a record high of 44.3202 trillion yen , due to the increase in energy demand , such as oil and natural gas , and the rise in prices .
in 2003 , japan 's trade surplus was 10.2378 trillion yen , up 3.6 percent from the previous year , and broke through the 10 trillion yen mark again in three years .
