xinhua news agency , guangzhou , january 26 ( chen ji and hu yanni ) according to information from the guangdong provincial administration of industry and commerce , the number of private enterprises in guangdong exceeded the number of state - owned and holding enterprises for the first time in 2003 , and domestic - funded enterprises have been effectively readjusted .
according to statistics , by the end of 2003 , there were 690,000 enterprises ( including domestic , private , and foreign - invested enterprises ) in the whole province , an increase of 0.59 percent over the end of last year .
among them , 3.16 million were domestic - funded enterprises , down 16.4 percent from the end of last year , with registered capital of 119.02 billion yuan , up 0.9 percent , while private enterprises increased by 24.9 percent and 33.8 percent , respectively , and foreign - funded enterprises increased by 3.6 percent and 4.1 percent , respectively .
for the first time , the number of privately - run enterprises has exceeded the number of state - owned and holding enterprises .
in the course of structural readjustment , the number of state - owned enterprises and their holding enterprises has decreased , but their strength has gradually increased , with the average registered capital ( gold ) reaching 3.76 million yuan , an increase of 20 percentage points over the end of 2002 .
according to statistics , in 2003 , the total number of newly registered enterprises of various types in the province was 105,000 , showing a situation of one drop and two rises .
among them , 17,000 domestic - funded enterprises , down 17.6 percent from the same period of last year , and 8,160 private enterprises and 6,561 foreign - invested enterprises , up 29 percent and 0.08 percent respectively .
the proportion of the number of domestic , private , and foreign - invested enterprises in the total number of newly registered enterprises is 16 : 78 : 6 .
( international ) the wto has submitted the " bird subsidies " dispute to arbitration for settlement
xinhua news agency , geneva , january 26 ( reporter li jie ) the world trade organization ( wto ) announced on the 26th that the eu and seven other wto members ' appeals for sanctions against the united states on " bird subsidies " have been submitted to the arbitration organization for adjudication .
this appeal of sanctions originated from the failure of the united states to abolish the " bird amendment " within the time limit set by the wto .
the " bird amendment " passed by the us congress in 2000 demanded that the us government give direct subsidies to us companies that have suffered losses in the antidumping and antisubsidy cases , instead of paying them to the us treasury department .
this move of the united states has met with opposition from major trade partners , including the european union and japan .
the wto finally concluded in january 2003 that the amendment was in violation of the global trade rules and demanded that the united states abolish it before december 27 , 2003 .
however , the united states did not enforce the wto decision .
for this reason , the european union , japan , canada , brazil , india , south korea , mexico , and chile recently applied to the wto for approval to levy additional tariffs equivalent to the amount of us government subsidies on some products from the united states .
however , the united states subsequently questioned the extent of the sanctions and the legality of the complaint .
