( international ) denmark introduces new bill to restrict immigration
xinhua news agency , stockholm , january 28 , the danish government today submitted a new bill to the parliament to restrict immigration .
under the bill , children born in denmark will no longer have the right to automatically obtain the danish nationality .
the bill is the latest move taken by danish freedom party leader rasmussen since he assumed the post of prime minister in november 2001 .
it is reported that the bill is likely to be passed by the parliament because the freedom party has won the support of the right - wing danish people 's party on the issue of immigration .
the bill requires the children of foreigners born in denmark to apply for nationality , but not to automatically obtain nationality , as those of other immigrants .
those who have acquired nationality will be deprived of their nationality if they have committed criminal crimes that pose serious harm to society .
in the past two years , the danish government has adopted a series of measures to restrict immigration , including restricting the issuance of long - term residence permits and restricting the entry of families into denmark .
the number of foreign victims in denmark dropped from 14,347 in 1993 to 3,500 in 2003 because of the danish government 's unwelcome attitude towards immigrants .
denmark 's freedom and the image of a human rights country have always been damaged .
singapore 's achievements cannot be regarded as a matter of course .
even if science and technology are developed , i do not believe that people can maintain an ideal environment of higher living standards and quality , the employment of the whole people , and the continuous increase in salaries without making efforts , maintaining social discipline , and adapting to changes .
these beautiful things can not be obtained naturally .
only when the whole people understand that they must attach importance to the interests of the community , make difficult compromise , and make necessary adjustments can they have a better future .
what will singapore do in a decade or so ?
we all hope to see the future , but it is hard to predict the future .
many factors are not under singapore 's control .
the development of many things depends on the development of the world situation .
we do n't know when there will be a problem , and many times this involves gas transportation .
for example , it is impossible to predict that three singapore people travel to hong kong , resulting in the infection of the saras virus .
in less than a month after the spring festival , three extraordinarily serious safety incidents have occurred in china , and dozens of people have died every time .
it is a pity that the accident occurred so frequently and the loss of life was so serious .
in the past few months , several incidents of pouring oil from the natural gas pipeline in chongqing , gas explosions in several coal mines , and frequent fatal traffic accidents have caused hundreds of deaths .
china has a vast territory , a dense population , and a greater probability of disasters than any other country , and it will lead to the death of dozens of people , even hundreds of people , and this is a reality that there is no alternative in objective conditions .
however , judging from the common sense , china 's fatal accidents are still too frequent .
among the many disasters , there were many fires , coal mine explosions , explosions at firecrackers factories , and passenger traffic accidents .
this shows at least two problems : one is that the safety measures in these areas are the most weak , and the other is that people have not drawn lessons from past tragedies , thus causing similar accidents to happen again and again .
at a time when singapore 's economy was growing at a high speed in the past , there were also serious fires , and the painful memory of the fire is still deep , but it has quickly raised singapore 's awareness of safety and prevention in public places .
at present , china is also in a very crucial period of rapid economic growth and great social transformation .
the number of accidents involving foreign domestic helpers who fell to work in hong kong has been heard from time to time , even though the figure is not high enough , the number of accidents in which the number of such accidents is far from meeting the work nature of the small number of casualties .
according to information , between january 1999 and june 2003 , a total of 99 female domestic helpers of various nationalities were killed in the accident .
behind these figures are the broken families that cannot wait for their daughter and mother to return home , and the misfortune that we should avoid one after another , and at the same time , we must do our best to reduce the number of regret to the minimum .
according to a recent statement issued by the indonesian embassy , 96 indonesian domestic helpers have been killed in singapore since 1999 , and some of them were killed when they were working in high - rise buildings .
in view of the accident , the indonesian government has expressed its dissatisfaction from time to time , and has formulated new regulations on many occasions to more strictly control the quality of local indonesian domestic helpers , but the problem has not been resolved , and the bilateral relationship between the two countries is bound to be disturbed by the problem of female domestic helpers .
what is deeply puzzling is that compared with the number of casualties in the construction sites , the number of female workers who fell to the building by accident is even higher , which makes people think deeply , and it is more necessary to study the background and cause of the accident .
chen kung - li , a well - known expert on the taiwan issue on the mainland of china , recently published a new book entitled " observe taiwan . "
most of the articles in the book were written after the first change of political parties in taiwan in march 2000 . as of the time when chen shui - bian put forward the theory of " one country on each side of the strait , " it was the author 's observation and consideration of taiwan 's internal situation and cross - strait relations during the period of " judging him by his deeds , not just by his words . "
the article , which was written two years ago , was published two years later . this shows that the mainland 's examination of taiwan - related studies is very complicated and the process is long , and it is even more evident that the " observation of taiwan " has not come easily .
for a long time , while observing and studying the taiwan issue , chen kung - li has always sought truth , pragmatism , and seeking truth from facts , and has not been restricted by any subjective political framework , and has worked hard to explore the penetrating insight of zhuo er .
after reading this book , this characteristic gives people a more profound impression .
after the early 1980 's , the study of the taiwan issue became the " obvious study " of the mainland . various research institutions have emerged one after another , and various kinds of scholars and experts have also displayed their talents .
overseas , people generally divide the mainland 's taiwan research institutions into the northern and southern factions .
the position of the north faction is relatively close to the government , and its remarks are relatively tough , and in some specific historical stages or major political developments , it has shown a more aggressive hawkish color .
taiwan research institutes in the south are generally distributed in areas south of the chang jiang , including shanghai and fujian .
the " academic qualifications " of japanese prime minister junichiro koizumi , who " has studied in london for two years , " have been exposed by japanese media as a matter of fact .
japan 's " post weekly " confirmed to the university of london that koizumi had only attended a few classes in britain for nine months and had not received any degree .
large and small media in china have vied with one another to report or download this scandal so that the broad masses of compatriots can enjoy popular support .
indeed , the prime minister of a country has gone so far as to fabricated false academic qualifications and deceive the people of the country .
in particular , japan , which is a " imperialist " country , is even more shameful .
however , if we can change the angle , perhaps we can see some positive significance from this scandal .
moreover , these positive things are precisely what we lack , and we need to improve .
in recent years , we have always advocated " honesty , " " building a sunshine government , " respecting the public 's " right to know , " and enhancing the " transparency " of administration . however , there is still a great gap between facts and ideals .
if you think about it , the diploma of a country 's prime minister is not that big , but it can be exposed by the media , and it is being pursued and fiercely attacked .
what else can a country like this not be " sunshine " ?
all major camps in taiwan will use tourist buses to send the masses to the meeting hall , but the recent situation is that the evening party of chen shui - bian and annette lu is obviously much lighter than that of lien chan and james soong .
not long ago , when taiwan president chen shui - bian [ chen shuibian ] went to a certain place in the northern part of the country to make a fuss about the situation , he said that half of the people in taiwan did not give the face to him . as a result , there were many relatives and friends of the local people who had invested in the mainland , and the three links were delayed again and again .
if there is no accident , it should be assumed that chen shui - bian - lu will be defeated when the presidential election enters the countdown , from the polls to the underground , and so on .
the fact that chen shui - bian , who has won a big position under lee teng - hui 's creation , has proved that he has not been able to effectively win the support of the people in the past four years . on the contrary , he has enabled the green camp to play the role and performances of all kinds of black money and low - taste , and has been constantly exposing to the public and weakening the confidence of the supporters .
in the face of the pan - blue forces that may be reruling , how should beijing look at it ?
first of all , it should be understood that the pan - blue army , which is likely to take power again , is no longer a pure one - party dominance of the kmt , but is the unity of the blue army , and the question of whether or not the internal tradition and the localization faction will merge .
close cooperation during the election period cannot be regarded as an inevitable relationship in the future .
if there is hope of winning the election , it is bound to take a considerable period of time to carry out internal integration , and the election of the legislative yuan at the end of the year will also make it very difficult for the lien - soong regime to make too important changes in cross - strait relations .
unless it can realize that the improvement of cross - strait relations can add to taiwan 's internal politics and that it is certain that it will be able to make achievements within a short period of time , and the most important thing is to let the people feel this achievement .
based on this background , beijing should temporarily postpone the action of promoting reunification and give lien chan and james soong , the leaders of the " traditional blue camp , " time to consolidate the internal situation .
more than half a century has passed since the united states carried out the first nuclear explosion in new mexico in july 1945 and dropped two atomic bombs on japan in august of the same year .
although the arms race between the two superpower of the united states and the soviet union has caused the accumulation of nuclear weapons to the extent that they are sufficient to destroy the whole world , both sides have realized the danger of a nuclear war and avoided pushing the button of nuclear war .
after the breakup of the soviet union and the entry of the world into the post - cold war era , the danger of a large - scale nuclear war has been basically eliminated .
at the same time , however , the danger of nuclear proliferation has increased rather than reduced .
this phenomenon of proliferation is manifested in two aspects .
first , some middle - level countries with considerable resources and strength , out of the purpose of regional hegemony , confrontation with neighboring countries , safeguarding security , or pursuing blackmail and diplomacy , are striving to produce and possess nuclear weapons through various means .
the other is that some non - state mass organizations , especially the islamic extremist forces with strong hatred for the western world , are also trying by every possible means to seek small nuclear weapons , and they do not hesitate to harm a large number of innocent people and carry out bloody terrorist activities against the west .
under this demand , the intermediaries engaged in the transfer and sale of nuclear weapons and related technology and the " nuclear black market " have come into being . moreover , the scale of nuclear weapons has been expanding with each passing day and has become an important part of the world 's nuclear proliferation at present .
as a descendant of the chinese people in the hangzhou jiahu area , the image of the rural areas south of the yangtze river and the life of the peasants in the old days are still in my memory .
when he returned to his hometown after the new year , he found that in the field of the shanghai - hangzhou expressway , which was full of green land , there were three - story buildings built by the peasants , but very few people were working on the ground .
this is really surprising to me , and it is hard to believe that such a great change will take place in the poe people , who are still very much in love in a foreign country .
however , recently , some reports on the situation in china 's rural areas and the on - the - spot investigation reports by scholars and scholars on the internet cannot help but feel greatly surprised and shocked .
it is not imagined that there are still such an unimaginable dark side in china 's rural areas , and the chinese peasants are still living a life of humiliation and difficulty .
after their on - the - spot interviews in the rural areas of anhui , henan , and hebei , chen guidi and his wife published a long report on " china 's rural investigation , " and asked for the peasants ' lives , which shocked the chinese society .
they have drawn the following conclusion from the large number of facts that the peasants were bullied by corrupt officials and even killed by innocent people : " when we approached the chinese peasants , we felt unprecedented shock and hidden pain . we have seen the poverty that you could not imagine , the crime that you could not imagine , and the failure to imagine , the resistance that we could not imagine , the silence that we could not imagine , and the sorrow that we could not imagine . "
this is really something that makes people soaked with blood .
unexpectedly , malaysian prime minister hamid albar announced the dissolution of the parliament monday , and a new general election will be held in the near future .
the election will be an event of great significance in his political career , and the result of the election will also be of symbolic significance to the political situation in malaysia and its development trend .
it has been only four months since he took over the leadership from mahathir in november last year .
in spite of this , he still decided to dissolve the parliament and hold a general election ahead of schedule .
this has at least two implications : first , agela is satisfied with his administrative performance in the past four months , and is full of confidence in the voters ' intention to vote , and second , he hopes to consolidate his power base through this means so that he can get out of the shadow of mahathir .
there is no doubt that the decision made by alpha to hold a flash - type election reflects that he has made a comprehensive assessment of the domestic political situation .
macedonia 's current economic situation is good , and there is no question of being exploited and used by the opposition parties .
in addition , since the beginning of his term of office , he has adopted a number of relatively high - visibility measures in the fight against corruption , including the arrest and prosecution of the former minister of land and cooperative development , and so on , which have won a certain degree of praise , and has also made the public optimistic about the future anti - corruption action .
at the same time , he called for improving the efficiency of civil service , which is also an encouraging move .
since its birth , the growth and formation of the european union has been strongly affected by france 's politics and culture .
in the diplomatic field , it is necessary to strive for independence and independence , and the attitude and method of handling world affairs are different from that of the united states . this is the direction of the eu 's foreign policy , and we can clearly see the shadow of france .
it is precisely for this reason that the international community , including china , russia , and arab countries , hopes to see the rise of the eu and see a completely independent force in international exchanges .
it must be acknowledged that since the end of the 1980 s , the eu has indeed made diplomatic efforts in this direction .
in december 1992 , the heads of state of the eu countries unanimously agreed at the madrid summit that all member states will implement a unified foreign policy so that they can speak in the same language .
however , two years later , when handling the issue of bosnia - herzegovina , the so - called " unified foreign policy " was completely defeated for the first time .
it can be said that the 10 - year - long eu diplomacy , from the madrid summit to today , is not worth mentioning .
in particular , the eu 's foreign policy cannot withstand the test of major events .
the different positions adopted by the member states in the us - iraq war have not only proved this point , but have also fully exposed the fatal political defects of the eu , that is , it is very easy for the eu to be separated by other big powers and to be destroyed by each other .
on 24 february , president bush announced at the white house that he would support the constitutional amendment banning the marriage of the same sex .
this is a marked change in his ambiguous attitude on this issue over the past few months and represents an important development of us politics in an election year .
the constitutional amendment , which prohibits the marriage of the same sex , is a very powerful political weapon in the southern part of the republican party , but it also plays a very great negative role in the united states , that is , in the whole country , this is a major cultural dispute of splitting public opinion , which will undoubtedly intensify the political polarization of the united states and further separate the east and west sides of the strait led by the liberal .
as far as bush himself , who repeatedly declared that he was a " member of the communist youth league " and not a " separatist , " was concerned , his words and deeds were obviously different .
in addition , the position of the younger generation in the united states on the issue of homosexuality has become increasingly open , and although bush 's move has short - term results , it will harm the long - term interests of the republican party .
bush 's new " constitutional amendment " offensive can be called the " jiaozuo strategy " of this year 's presidential election .
bush has adopted this strategy because he has become increasingly weak on the two important topics of " anti - terrorism " war and economic - employment , and has to open up a new battlefield on the religious and cultural issues of splitting the public opinion at home .
so far , the united states has remained cautious .
in other words , since maintaining the status quo in the taiwan strait can satisfy the united states ' long - term strategic goal of containing the mainland , the united states should avoid political and military conflicts with china because it encourages taiwan independence .
it can be imagined that it is impossible for the united states to completely eliminate the space for holding a referendum in taiwan in accordance with beijing 's demands , but out of consideration for its own interests , it will also take some early warning actions .
recently , us secretary of state powell took the initiative to reiterate the established policy toward taiwan and made clear the us stand of opposing taiwan independence .
this kind of attitude has been interpreted by the outside world as aimed at containing and preventing chen shui - bian from being possessed by the devil .
the recent remarks made by some us think tank figures with official background and the fact that the united states will send a large number of spy ships to the taiwan strait in the near future to detect cross - strait military movements have indirectly proved that the united states is very concerned about the situation in the taiwan strait .
from another angle , it shows that although the united states will not completely stop taiwan from holding a referendum in accordance with beijing 's demand , it is also worried about the uncertainty of the situation in the taiwan strait during this period .
in the end , any large - scale and one - to - one election can only produce one result , either chen shui - bian is lucky enough to win a second term , or lien chan is returning to taiwan 's presidential palace .
what is worrying is that under the condition of asymmetrical information dissemination , people of all walks of life on the mainland do not seem to be mentally prepared for chen shui - bian 's possible victory .
if the result of the election is not what it wishes , then beijing will once again fall into an unnecessary passive position .
an arab ancient saying goes : " a day of chaos is even more terrible than the 1,000 - year - old government . "
is this what the northeast asian countries are worried about now ?
i think the answer is probably certain .
a well - known research and development center , which is close to washington and sponsored by the us government , has explored four policy options for dealing with the north korean nuclear crisis , namely , exchanges , containment , economic sanctions , and preemptive attacks .
the focus of the survey is on the attitudes of countries in the region towards these strategies .
in addition , the survey also analyzed the threat posed by the dprk 's nuclear weapons program in light of the possibility of nuclear attack by the people of the dprk 's neighboring countries and the damage they may cause , as well as their fear .
china and russia feel that the danger of north korea 's use of nuclear weapons is low or very low , while japan and south korea believe that the threat is quite great .
all northeast asian countries agree to maintain contacts with the dprk .
japan , on the other hand , supports containment , and other countries also believe that under certain circumstances , the containment strategy is acceptable .
singapore is very concerned about the international ranking , and has paid great attention to the list of countries in europe and the united states .
we are always in the forefront , and naturally we have increased our interest in ranking .
however , the first thing is a lot of worries .
the ordinary people feel that they are afraid of losing too much attention to the ranking , and they are proud of showing their own ranking .
therefore , people say that we should live a better life , and it is better to compete with the rest of the world .
since many people have been very disrespectful to their ranking in the past , a wonderful phenomenon has emerged : it seems that people no longer regard " world number one " as good news , but are more inclined to regard it as an embarrassing thing .
however , the situation has changed again in the past one or two years .
we have doubts about the long - term competitiveness of the country , and people from all walks of life are also worried that their own rice bowl will be difficult to secure .
with this doubt , we are no longer so casual when we talk .
international competition is fierce , and too narrow and casual may cause others to catch up with each other , and first , it is easy to become a sample that is backward .
