opponents in the us presidential election in 2004 have been confirmed : democratic candidate kerry challenges republican incumbent president bush .
before the general election in november , they began to carry out " warm - up activities " such as advertising and campaign debates .
they will probably be engaged in verbal and written confrontations on the three major issues of war , economy , and society .
bush believes that war is closely related to us national security , and sending troops to overthrow saddam and counter - terrorism are all aimed at ensuring us security . therefore , he has kept telling our countrymen : " we are in war . "
kerry will naturally point out that bush abused the wrong intelligence of iraq 's possession of weapons of mass destruction to launch a war against iraq .
on the economy , kerry believes that bush 's tax cut plan is beneficial to the rich and cannot create new employment opportunities .
bush called kerry , " is n't the current us economic data being promoted ? "
in terms of social issues , the relationship between men and women , bush is opposed to the marriage of the same sex , the abortion , and the death penalty , and kerry is also against the marriage of the same sex , but he is in favor of abortion and the death penalty .
how bush and kerry will give their respective views on these three major issues and convince the voters through advertisements , television , and speeches is the political show they are going to perform in the next eight months .
however , on diplomatic issues , kerry has more room to sell his skills .
according to information , most of the young people who choose to commit suicide are young people aged between 15 and 19 , but many are young people aged between 10 and 14 .
it is generally believed that academic pressure is the cause of child and youth suicide , but the study found that emotional problems , especially the problem of love between men and women , and the problem of living with parents , are the main reasons for the local young people to find their own shortcomings .
of course , the gap between academic pressure and expectations is also within the scope of communication between parents and children .
the pressure of further studies is an unavoidable burden for local students for a long time , and sometimes the pressure is given to them , and many of them are on their parents and children .
it is true that the parents demand that their children have good results and that they make a comparison with other children , and ask their children to strive for the upper reaches . however , the channel of persuasion and communication behind the pressure is the only way to measure the temperature of their children 's relations .
if the children 's performance is not ideal , their parents will make a silent criticism , or even make their children feel that they are disappointing , and no doubt they will push their children to the state of being unable to seek help .
it is understood that many young students who need to receive guidance have been forced into the blind corner by their parents ' excessively high expectations .
the success and rapid development of singapore have made parents feel that the current material conditions of children are much better than in the past , and it is inevitable that children should perform better than themselves .
normally , when parents forget that they are still children , in fact , their performance in various aspects may not be particularly outstanding .
by the age of one and a half , the overwhelming majority of children were sent to the child care center of various organs and units , and the authorities had only a symbolic charge of a little child , a week or even a month before they returned to their homes .
today , singapore is facing a social problem of a declining fertility rate and an aging population .
in order to maintain modern living standards and fashion - oriented material , the younger generation is unable to take care of themselves , and no one has the energy to respond to the government 's call for early marriage and early birth .
the author has a bold suggestion : the government should take over the new - born children .
the people of our country only take care of their own life and do not have to worry about the issue of raising children .
on the one hand , the government has set up an all - embracing kindergarten , changed primary schools into whole - day schools , and even provided three - meal services , thus providing a symbolic charge to the citizens .
this will not only solve the employment problem of the unemployed population , but also do not require the government to worry about the effectiveness of such measures as giving bonuses to babies , increasing paternity leave , improving the quality of women 's helpers , and tax rebate .
