specifically speaking , on the one hand , beijing wants to urge the dprk to give up its nuclear weapons , and on the other hand , starting from the transformation of the kim chong - il regime , it will take the road of modern civilization , lift the danger of a nuclear war in northeast asia , maintain the status quo on the korean peninsula , and gain the bargaining chips for long - term strategic dealings with the united states .
pyongyang appears to be tough in appearance but is weak in essence , and it is very eager to develop its economy and merge with the international community .
however , such a desire is often manifested in the external form of being strong , irrational , and sometimes even totally inconsistent with international rules .
in fact , for a period of time , beijing has used its influence and economic aid to force pyongyang to change its stand that does not conform to international rules .
however , this action still needs all - round planning .
beijing 's aid to pyongyang should not be confined to the economic level , but should also be extended to other social sectors , and should not be confined to pyongyang 's abandonment of its nuclear program , and should all the more focus on leading it to the road of modern civilization .
