china 's policy of reform and opening up began from agriculture , and rural residents were the first to benefit from this policy .
however , since the 1990 's , due to the fact that economic policies have been tilted toward cities by a large margin , agricultural reform has basically been in a state of stagnation , and the gap between urban and rural areas has been widening .
for a long time , china has seen two completely different world situations : one is a highly prosperous city , and the other is a poor and backward village .
in the words of chinese officials , the widening gap between the rich and the poor in china 's urban and rural areas is a " problem of development , " so it is still necessary to resolve it through sustained development .
in other words , china 's coastal areas and cities should continue to develop , and should not be dragged down by rural problems .
however , when some big cities can see a small change every year and a big change in three years , people cannot help but ask : why has there been no change in some impoverished areas in the past few decades ?
of course , the development channels of urban and rural areas are very different , and this is a fact that should be recognized . however , the question is : when we invest a large amount of funds in urban construction and encourage and support the rich middle class , will the rural population , which accounts for 70 percent of the country 's total population , also be concerned about and attach importance to it ?
theoretically , all previous chinese governments have attached great importance to the issues of agriculture , rural areas , and peasants .
however , over the past few years , the situation in the rural areas has become increasingly difficult and deteriorating , and this shows that the degree of importance it has attached is not enough .
in any country , public security , procuratorial , and judicial organs should be a symbol of justice and justice , as well as the most important system for ensuring social stability .
unfortunately , however , public security , procuratorial , and judicial organs have become a symbol of corruption in china .
according to a recent report by the state auditing administration , the results of the examination of the financial expenditure of public security organs in 26 provinces and municipalities last year showed that the amount of public security organs in the country had exceeded 16.5 billion yuan .
the crisis of trust in public security , procuratorial , and judicial organs has been made public .
the liu yong incident , the sun zhigang incident , and the recent " bmw " incident in heilongjiang all reflect this profound distrust .
the " bmw " incident is even more typical .
people 's attention to this issue has even far exceeded their concern about " sars " during the " sars " period .
as a matter of fact , people 's concern is no longer the " bmw " incident itself , but has expressed their distrust of the entire judicial system .
relevant departments are very clear about this , so they have taken measures to stop the media shortly .
however , the problem is still there .
the second round of six - party talks on the nuclear issue on the korean peninsula ended in the expected results .
during the talks , the parties concerned had contacts and explorations on the peripheral issues of the nuclear crisis on the peninsula , and reached a consensus on the third round of talks and the establishment of a working group before the end of june this year .
however , on such substantive issues as how the dprk should give up its nuclear weapons development program , how the united states should ensure the political and military security of the dprk after the dprk gives up its nuclear program , and how to provide energy aid to the dprk , the talks not only did not make progress , but also gave the people the feeling that the " dead knot " has become increasingly tense .
the two main players , the dprk and the united states , did not make any concessions , nor did they relax their basic positions .
however , what has attracted people 's attention is that during the talks , the united states displayed an attitude of not being eager to resolve problems and gave people an impression of " delaying . "
this strategy displayed by the united states is closely related to the new development of the current international situation and the interests it has sought in these new developments .
since roosevelt became president , the united states has never put so many corporate bosses in jail .
is this a coincidence , or is it that the public and investors have gone beyond forbearance in the past three years in dealing with corporate crimes and other illegal activities , which have recently been exposed one after another ?
the answer may not be simple , but the criminal acts of many companies have been exposed recently .
this is a good beginning for the economic recovery , especially for the restoration of investment confidence .
at the end of the 1990s , it may be one of the most chaotic and hard to find in the us commercial history , and the sooner the impact will disappear , the better .
when the dust is settled , the names of some companies will surely be weakened into history , and they can only be found in the textbooks of the business school .
some other companies , such as taike and mmc , will , under the leadership of the new management team , strive to reorganize to greet the arrival of a new round of economic growth .
when will a new round of economic growth come ?
as the wto , you may have no answer .
this is not necessary because us federal reserve chairman greenspan does not know the answer either .
the bush administration is trying to stimulate the economy by means of keenness , and on the one hand , it is making great efforts to increase spending ( especially national defense spending ) , and on the other hand , it is reducing taxes by a large margin .
internationally , the bush administration has continued to pursue free trade , but the trade deficit has reached a new high of $ 549 billion .
after a big tax cut , investment and consumption did not increase significantly .
the new kiss school , represented by the famous british economist gao shangquan , believes that the us economy has been bogged down in a predicament and that bush 's financial and economic strategy is lacking .
they believe that the so - called " market law in command " is only an illusion , which will inevitably lead to the benefit of a small number of people and the loss of the majority .
in the past , people believed that on a global scale , the so - called minority of people who have made profits are all in the united states , and the majority of people who have suffered losses are developing countries .
this is not the case at present .
many people in the us economic circles believe that apart from the multinational corporations based on the united states , india and china are also in a prominent position in the current globalization .
india occupies the service economy and china occupies the manufacturing sector .
people are concentrating their energies on the large - scale transfer of us capital and production equipment to china , but they do not see the advantages of china 's high - level and low - income labor market .
first of all , whether taiwan 's current situation is within beijing 's estimate or outside beijing 's estimate .
how beijing estimates , only it is clear itself , but the estimated results can be considered by other people from the open phenomenon .
over the past four years , the independence camp of chen shui - bian and annette lu has made clear - cut remarks and has worked hard , and the taiwan independence movement has made positive progress .
on the other hand , beijing 's attitude is close to routine , and it seems that it is indifferent to the progress of taiwan independence .
however , since the fall of last year , it has become completely different . it seems that the cars have changed . in the past few months , it has been evident that the handling capacity is quite different from that of the 1990 's .
based on this , we can predict that the current situation in taiwan is within its estimate .
second , we will look at taiwan - related diplomacy .
with regard to the development of the situation in the taiwan strait , we should see that the attitude of the united states and other major countries is relatively close to beijing and is relatively close to taipei .
since the attitude of various countries is open to the public , the answer is very clear .
so far , various countries and beijing have not only become relatively close to each other , but also have a lot of concrete common points . they have become rather far away from taipei , and their specific common points are relatively small . moreover , they have also begun to give advice on taiwan 's democracy , which has always been praised .
